Hi, everybody.

00:02:11.009 --> 00:02:13.463 align:middle line:10%
We're here in absolutely
stunningly beautiful Sardinia.

00:02:13.463 --> 00:02:16.130 align:middle line:10%
And today I'm with Freddy Silva,
who we've been out in the field

00:02:16.130 --> 00:02:16.930 align:middle line:10%
together.

00:02:16.930 --> 00:02:18.710 align:middle line:10%
We've made some
stunning discoveries

00:02:18.710 --> 00:02:21.080 align:middle line:10%
which we're going to be
talking about in just a sec.

00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:24.380 align:middle line:84%
First, I want to get some
of your impressions about--

00:02:24.380 --> 00:02:27.260 align:middle line:84%
your first impressions
about being out in the field

00:02:27.260 --> 00:02:31.160 align:middle line:84%
just among this raw land
and these ancient sites.

00:02:31.160 --> 00:02:33.560 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It was nice
being in a place

00:02:33.560 --> 00:02:36.080 align:middle line:84%
where you know
very little about,

00:02:36.080 --> 00:02:37.970 align:middle line:84%
or little has been
written about,

00:02:37.970 --> 00:02:39.440 align:middle line:90%
and it's full of surprises.

00:02:39.440 --> 00:02:41.540 align:middle line:84%
It's blowing my mind
every single time.

00:02:41.540 --> 00:02:43.250 align:middle line:84%
The age of things,
such as the fact

00:02:43.250 --> 00:02:46.150 align:middle line:84%
that we're sitting on the oldest
rocks in Europe to begin with,

00:02:46.150 --> 00:02:47.150 align:middle line:90%
which is quite stunning.

00:02:47.150 --> 00:02:48.650 align:middle line:90%
The landscape is extraordinary.

00:02:48.650 --> 00:02:50.600 align:middle line:84%
But it's the level
and depth of history

00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:53.040 align:middle line:84%
that's here that few
people know about.

00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:55.760 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of rare to be in that
situation in the 21st century

00:02:55.760 --> 00:02:57.838 align:middle line:84%
where you go somewhere
and you can think, oh,

00:02:57.838 --> 00:02:59.630 align:middle line:84%
we have raw material
here we can work with.

00:02:59.630 --> 00:03:00.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:03:00.530 --> 00:03:01.500 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I was shocked.

00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:02.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: How we're
connected to other things.

00:03:02.240 --> 00:03:03.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:03:03.040 --> 00:03:05.600 align:middle line:84%
And researching, you know for
yourself, starting to research

00:03:05.600 --> 00:03:06.740 align:middle line:90%
before we came here.

00:03:06.740 --> 00:03:10.650 align:middle line:84%
They never really spoke a
lot about the nuraghe even.

00:03:10.650 --> 00:03:11.450 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: No.

00:03:11.450 --> 00:03:13.760 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, by the
time the Greeks show up,

00:03:13.760 --> 00:03:16.083 align:middle line:84%
people just had these
myths and stories to tell,

00:03:16.083 --> 00:03:17.750 align:middle line:84%
and there was
superstition about things.

00:03:17.750 --> 00:03:19.492 align:middle line:84%
In fact, no one
even remembers why

00:03:19.492 --> 00:03:21.200 align:middle line:84%
they were called the
towers of the giants

00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:22.325 align:middle line:90%
or the tombs of the giants.

00:03:22.325 --> 00:03:25.370 align:middle line:84%
It seems to have been in the
vernacular, in the folklore.

00:03:25.370 --> 00:03:27.890 align:middle line:84%
But it was so lost to
history in the mist of time

00:03:27.890 --> 00:03:29.450 align:middle line:90%
that they're just stories.

00:03:29.450 --> 00:03:30.950 align:middle line:84%
But the stories
is where we begin

00:03:30.950 --> 00:03:32.510 align:middle line:84%
because those are
the things that

00:03:32.510 --> 00:03:34.520 align:middle line:84%
contain the kernel
of the information

00:03:34.520 --> 00:03:35.520 align:middle line:90%
that we're looking for.

00:03:35.520 --> 00:03:36.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:38.030 align:middle line:84%
And that was so
interesting going out

00:03:38.030 --> 00:03:41.480 align:middle line:84%
in the field in our last
episode, talking with Luigi

00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:43.400 align:middle line:84%
whose family
history is very much

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:46.730 align:middle line:84%
tied to what some call
the legends of the giants.

00:03:46.730 --> 00:03:47.810 align:middle line:90%
And they say, no.

00:03:47.810 --> 00:03:49.520 align:middle line:90%
These are our ancestors.

00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:52.430 align:middle line:10%
So first of all, what was
interesting is I called you,

00:03:52.430 --> 00:03:56.300 align:middle line:10%
and you had just finished this
book called "Missing Lands."

00:03:56.300 --> 00:03:59.060 align:middle line:10%
And I thought, how
convenient is this?

00:03:59.060 --> 00:04:00.920 align:middle line:10%
"Missing Lands" is
coming out right

00:04:00.920 --> 00:04:04.400 align:middle line:10%
when we call you to see about
looking for what might be

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:06.240 align:middle line:10%
another of the missing lands.

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:07.040 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:08.945 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the thing
that fascinates me

00:04:08.945 --> 00:04:10.820 align:middle line:84%
about the research into
ancient civilizations

00:04:10.820 --> 00:04:12.620 align:middle line:84%
and a missing
civilization at that

00:04:12.620 --> 00:04:15.650 align:middle line:84%
was that we've been so focused
on things like Atlantis

00:04:15.650 --> 00:04:17.089 align:middle line:90%
or Lemuria.

00:04:17.089 --> 00:04:19.700 align:middle line:84%
But we've blinkered
ourselves to the point where

00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:21.180 align:middle line:90%
we don't think beyond that.

00:04:21.180 --> 00:04:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And it's been an
extraordinary revelation

00:04:23.300 --> 00:04:26.000 align:middle line:84%
to realize that there are
other places that are missing.

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:27.770 align:middle line:84%
There are other
stories which talk

00:04:27.770 --> 00:04:30.140 align:middle line:84%
about missing people
and missing sages

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:32.150 align:middle line:84%
and magicians and
priests that came

00:04:32.150 --> 00:04:33.890 align:middle line:84%
from different
parts of the world.

00:04:33.890 --> 00:04:35.930 align:middle line:84%
Seven of them, as far
as I can figure out.

00:04:35.930 --> 00:04:38.473 align:middle line:84%
And I think Sardinia kind
of fits into this paradigm.

00:04:38.473 --> 00:04:39.890 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of
things here which

00:04:39.890 --> 00:04:42.980 align:middle line:84%
seem to fit in very
nicely with the stories

00:04:42.980 --> 00:04:46.580 align:middle line:84%
that we hear in other parts of
the world, as far away as Peru,

00:04:46.580 --> 00:04:49.430 align:middle line:84%
as far away as Easter
Island and even Orkney.

00:04:49.430 --> 00:04:52.400 align:middle line:84%
So there's something here that
obviously merits attention.

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:53.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:04:53.360 --> 00:04:56.038 align:middle line:84%
So Freddy, first of all, why
did you write "Missing Lands?"

00:04:56.038 --> 00:04:57.830 align:middle line:84%
We're going to tie that
story in because it

00:04:57.830 --> 00:04:59.690 align:middle line:84%
lays a really nice
backdrop for what we're

00:04:59.690 --> 00:05:01.357 align:middle line:84%
going to see when we
go out in the field

00:05:01.357 --> 00:05:03.167 align:middle line:84%
with these incredible
ancient sites.

00:05:03.167 --> 00:05:05.750 align:middle line:84%
What were you trying to bring
to the world in "Missing Lands?"

00:05:05.750 --> 00:05:07.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: The humanity of it.

00:05:07.420 --> 00:05:09.680 align:middle line:84%
We hear so much about
Plato and we hear so much

00:05:09.680 --> 00:05:12.382 align:middle line:84%
about things which he had done
on a very scholarly level,

00:05:12.382 --> 00:05:14.090 align:middle line:84%
but there's a humanity
missing, you know?

00:05:14.090 --> 00:05:15.260 align:middle line:84%
And for me it was
about the people.

00:05:15.260 --> 00:05:17.480 align:middle line:84%
Who were these people that
we keep talking about?

00:05:17.480 --> 00:05:19.370 align:middle line:10%
There are these
missing civilizations

00:05:19.370 --> 00:05:22.460 align:middle line:10%
that we hear about, the
Anu and the Anunnaki.

00:05:22.460 --> 00:05:25.490 align:middle line:10%
And they begin a very
bad sort of time--

00:05:25.490 --> 00:05:27.365 align:middle line:10%
PR, in terms of PR.

00:05:27.365 --> 00:05:29.240 align:middle line:84%
They're always seen in
a very negative light.

00:05:29.240 --> 00:05:31.490 align:middle line:84%
That wasn't my intention at
all, and it wasn't certainly

00:05:31.490 --> 00:05:32.360 align:middle line:90%
my impression.

00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:35.450 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to bring that
out in a positive way,

00:05:35.450 --> 00:05:37.730 align:middle line:84%
in the way that was written
a long, long time ago,

00:05:37.730 --> 00:05:39.740 align:middle line:84%
and connect all those
dots and figure out,

00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:41.067 align:middle line:90%
why were these people here?

00:05:41.067 --> 00:05:41.900 align:middle line:90%
Where did they live?

00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:43.130 align:middle line:90%
What was their purpose?

00:05:43.130 --> 00:05:45.930 align:middle line:84%
And why did they live separately
from the rest of the human race

00:05:45.930 --> 00:05:46.730 align:middle line:90%
all the time?

00:05:46.730 --> 00:05:48.590 align:middle line:84%
They seemed to be on
islands all the time.

00:05:48.590 --> 00:05:50.780 align:middle line:84%
They seemed to keep
away from humanity,

00:05:50.780 --> 00:05:53.810 align:middle line:84%
but they were very much focused
on the development of humanity.

00:05:53.810 --> 00:05:55.310 align:middle line:84%
They were very
concerned about where

00:05:55.310 --> 00:05:57.170 align:middle line:84%
we were going from
hunter gatherers

00:05:57.170 --> 00:05:59.580 align:middle line:90%
into another level of education.

00:05:59.580 --> 00:06:01.830 align:middle line:84%
So that's what fascinated
me about the whole thing.

00:06:01.830 --> 00:06:04.130 align:middle line:84%
And again, I never
have any idea where

00:06:04.130 --> 00:06:05.420 align:middle line:90%
I'm going with these projects.

00:06:05.420 --> 00:06:08.123 align:middle line:84%
I let the story and the
evidence reveal itself

00:06:08.123 --> 00:06:09.290 align:middle line:90%
and see how it all connects.

00:06:09.290 --> 00:06:11.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, you follow
the breadcrumbs, basically.

00:06:11.330 --> 00:06:11.780 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:06:11.780 --> 00:06:13.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then
start tying it together.

00:06:13.220 --> 00:06:15.012 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: A piece of
bread from breadcrumbs.

00:06:15.012 --> 00:06:17.102 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes the bread
crumbs end up nowhere,

00:06:17.102 --> 00:06:18.060 align:middle line:90%
and you just let it go.

00:06:18.060 --> 00:06:20.180 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes the
breadcrumbs do come together

00:06:20.180 --> 00:06:22.790 align:middle line:84%
and you start putting together
this wonderful recipe,

00:06:22.790 --> 00:06:25.250 align:middle line:90%
and it speaks for itself.

00:06:25.250 --> 00:06:27.000 align:middle line:90%
You take your ego out of it.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:28.970 align:middle line:84%
You let the people
in the old days--

00:06:28.970 --> 00:06:31.580 align:middle line:84%
not the scholars, because so
much of what we know today

00:06:31.580 --> 00:06:34.760 align:middle line:84%
comes from a westerly,
Anglo-Saxon approach,

00:06:34.760 --> 00:06:36.290 align:middle line:90%
and they always never--

00:06:36.290 --> 00:06:38.435 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Total scientific
materialism, you know?

00:06:38.435 --> 00:06:40.670 align:middle line:84%
Trying to date things,
carbon date things that

00:06:40.670 --> 00:06:42.170 align:middle line:90%
can't be carbon dated even.

00:06:42.170 --> 00:06:42.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:06:42.590 --> 00:06:43.070 align:middle line:90%
Like rocks.

00:06:43.070 --> 00:06:43.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:06:43.580 --> 00:06:43.895 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:06:43.895 --> 00:06:44.720 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:44.720 --> 00:06:46.280 align:middle line:84%
And then when were
the rocks actually

00:06:46.280 --> 00:06:47.520 align:middle line:90%
chiseled in place there?

00:06:47.520 --> 00:06:48.770 align:middle line:90%
That's a whole other subject.

00:06:48.770 --> 00:06:51.560 align:middle line:84%
So you identified
seven different kind

00:06:51.560 --> 00:06:55.580 align:middle line:84%
of-- what some call the navel
centers of modern civilization.

00:06:55.580 --> 00:06:58.880 align:middle line:84%
And modern means essentially
after the great deluge,

00:06:58.880 --> 00:07:00.960 align:middle line:84%
about 11,000, 12,000
years ago, right?

00:07:00.960 --> 00:07:01.760 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:07:01.760 --> 00:07:05.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So after that,
we sometimes tap into

00:07:05.360 --> 00:07:06.350 align:middle line:90%
what happened before.

00:07:06.350 --> 00:07:10.410 align:middle line:84%
It's very difficult because the
world was covered in mud, OK?

00:07:10.410 --> 00:07:14.080 align:middle line:84%
And you and I talked about this
out in the field quite a bit.

00:07:14.080 --> 00:07:16.400 align:middle line:84%
What we're looking
at as our evidence

00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:17.960 align:middle line:90%
is only what we can see.

00:07:17.960 --> 00:07:20.660 align:middle line:84%
So much layered, all
these civilizations

00:07:20.660 --> 00:07:21.800 align:middle line:90%
layered underneath it.

00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:25.520 align:middle line:84%
And let's for a moment go
back to the Atlantis myth

00:07:25.520 --> 00:07:28.460 align:middle line:84%
because in Sardinia, they do
not believe this is a myth.

00:07:28.460 --> 00:07:31.970 align:middle line:10%
Nor did Plato, nor did
Aristotle, nor did Herodotus.

00:07:31.970 --> 00:07:35.150 align:middle line:10%
They all believe
Sardinia was Atlantis.

00:07:35.150 --> 00:07:38.990 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about the
Atlantis-Sardinia interface

00:07:38.990 --> 00:07:41.480 align:middle line:90%
from your perspective.

00:07:41.480 --> 00:07:43.880 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: There's a certain
overlap that happens here.

00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:46.830 align:middle line:84%
The Egyptians basically were
telling Solon the story,

00:07:46.830 --> 00:07:48.080 align:middle line:90%
and Solon gives it to his son.

00:07:48.080 --> 00:07:49.400 align:middle line:90%
His son gives it to Plato.

00:07:49.400 --> 00:07:52.070 align:middle line:84%
Plato uses the mechanism
of myth in order

00:07:52.070 --> 00:07:54.470 align:middle line:84%
to make sort of a play
out of it in a way

00:07:54.470 --> 00:07:55.820 align:middle line:90%
that you can remember the story.

00:07:55.820 --> 00:07:59.063 align:middle line:84%
And they were in no uncertainty
that the land originally

00:07:59.063 --> 00:08:00.480 align:middle line:84%
was in the middle
of the Atlantic,

00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:01.940 align:middle line:90%
which is where it gets its name.

00:08:01.940 --> 00:08:04.400 align:middle line:84%
The same story appears
in the Yucatan as well.

00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:07.460 align:middle line:84%
The people of Atel, which
is what they called it.

00:08:07.460 --> 00:08:09.560 align:middle line:84%
But what we don't
seem to understand

00:08:09.560 --> 00:08:12.800 align:middle line:84%
is that the empire upon
which Atlantis was based

00:08:12.800 --> 00:08:14.180 align:middle line:90%
was spread out throughout the--

00:08:14.180 --> 00:08:15.847 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this
is the key point here

00:08:15.847 --> 00:08:18.200 align:middle line:84%
and where people get confused,
like the Roman Empire.

00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:20.420 align:middle line:84%
No, Britain wasn't
Rome, but it did

00:08:20.420 --> 00:08:23.050 align:middle line:84%
have Roman presence, Roman
features, and roads and so

00:08:23.050 --> 00:08:23.850 align:middle line:90%
forth.

00:08:23.850 --> 00:08:25.310 align:middle line:90%
So let's pick it up from there.

00:08:25.310 --> 00:08:26.340 align:middle line:90%
I agree with you.

00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:28.670 align:middle line:84%
And that was what intrigued
me about doing this story,

00:08:28.670 --> 00:08:30.770 align:middle line:84%
because of the
story of the giants

00:08:30.770 --> 00:08:32.720 align:middle line:84%
and even in biblical
texts talking

00:08:32.720 --> 00:08:35.270 align:middle line:84%
about the presence
of giants on Earth

00:08:35.270 --> 00:08:39.830 align:middle line:84%
and giants on Atlantis in
the day, and then the giants

00:08:39.830 --> 00:08:42.590 align:middle line:84%
here in the story that this
was believed to be Atlantis.

00:08:42.590 --> 00:08:44.990 align:middle line:84%
This all became the
point of intrigue for me.

00:08:44.990 --> 00:08:47.330 align:middle line:84%
So pick it up and talk
about these places

00:08:47.330 --> 00:08:50.400 align:middle line:84%
that the Atlanteans had
outposts, so to speak.

00:08:50.400 --> 00:08:51.200 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:08:51.200 --> 00:08:53.600 align:middle line:84%
I mean, their empire
apparently covered Libya.

00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:55.250 align:middle line:10%
Not the country
that we know today,

00:08:55.250 --> 00:08:58.100 align:middle line:10%
but Libya was basically
the whole of North Africa.

00:08:58.100 --> 00:09:01.970 align:middle line:10%
It was extended through Menorca
and Mallorca, part of which

00:09:01.970 --> 00:09:03.270 align:middle line:10%
are now sunk as well.

00:09:03.270 --> 00:09:05.270 align:middle line:84%
And they also covered
a lot of the territory

00:09:05.270 --> 00:09:07.130 align:middle line:84%
around the Mediterranean,
the coastline.

00:09:07.130 --> 00:09:09.920 align:middle line:10%
So that essentially-- the
Atlantean empire, according

00:09:09.920 --> 00:09:12.620 align:middle line:10%
to the traditions,
almost abutted

00:09:12.620 --> 00:09:16.610 align:middle line:10%
the Egyptian empire, which
itself is dated about 36,000

00:09:16.610 --> 00:09:18.985 align:middle line:10%
BC, according to
the King List, which

00:09:18.985 --> 00:09:20.360 align:middle line:10%
has written in
the Turin papyrus.

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:22.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And according to the
hermetics, even further back.

00:09:22.550 --> 00:09:23.000 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:23.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:23.300 --> 00:09:25.970 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So we're talking about
a very long time, most of which

00:09:25.970 --> 00:09:28.740 align:middle line:84%
has been lost because
of constant catastrophe.

00:09:28.740 --> 00:09:29.540 align:middle line:90%
That's the problem.

00:09:29.540 --> 00:09:31.430 align:middle line:84%
We're looking for things
under the surface,

00:09:31.430 --> 00:09:32.930 align:middle line:90%
literally and metaphorically.

00:09:32.930 --> 00:09:33.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:09:33.830 --> 00:09:37.100 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So you had this
essence of a concept

00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:39.960 align:middle line:90%
of an influence of an empire.

00:09:39.960 --> 00:09:42.358 align:middle line:84%
But what I like to
look at is the myths,

00:09:42.358 --> 00:09:44.150 align:middle line:84%
because the myths are
a wonderful mechanism

00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:45.740 align:middle line:90%
for recording great information.

00:09:45.740 --> 00:09:48.830 align:middle line:84%
But you have to understand what
the myth is trying to tell you

00:09:48.830 --> 00:09:51.620 align:middle line:84%
and the language and the
symbology used in the myth.

00:09:51.620 --> 00:09:53.308 align:middle line:84%
And once you start
doing that, once you

00:09:53.308 --> 00:09:55.100 align:middle line:84%
start getting into the
nitty gritty of what

00:09:55.100 --> 00:09:56.780 align:middle line:84%
the myth is saying,
you can compare it

00:09:56.780 --> 00:09:58.040 align:middle line:90%
to other parts of the world.

00:09:58.040 --> 00:09:59.600 align:middle line:84%
And in Sardinia
especially, there's

00:09:59.600 --> 00:10:02.600 align:middle line:84%
a lot of overlaps with other
stories from other parts

00:10:02.600 --> 00:10:05.990 align:middle line:84%
of the world, and it talks about
this worldwide brotherhood.

00:10:05.990 --> 00:10:06.890 align:middle line:90%
And sisterhood.

00:10:06.890 --> 00:10:08.390 align:middle line:84%
There was all-- the
woman was always

00:10:08.390 --> 00:10:09.473 align:middle line:90%
the central issue in this.

00:10:09.473 --> 00:10:13.088 align:middle line:84%
She always held the wisdom
of the entire brotherhood.

00:10:13.088 --> 00:10:14.630 align:middle line:84%
But there were these
groups of people

00:10:14.630 --> 00:10:16.463 align:middle line:84%
who I never thought
were actually connected,

00:10:16.463 --> 00:10:18.020 align:middle line:84%
but it turns out
they all are, which

00:10:18.020 --> 00:10:19.860 align:middle line:84%
is another reason
for writing the book.

00:10:19.860 --> 00:10:22.640 align:middle line:84%
It was about showing how
it wasn't just the Anu.

00:10:22.640 --> 00:10:24.800 align:middle line:84%
It was also about the
people of the serpent

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:26.840 align:middle line:84%
and all these other
people who were--

00:10:26.840 --> 00:10:30.200 align:middle line:84%
we talked about the Viracocha,
for example, who were also

00:10:30.200 --> 00:10:31.550 align:middle line:90%
called the Shining Ones.

00:10:31.550 --> 00:10:33.200 align:middle line:84%
Well, those appear
in the Middle East.

00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:36.230 align:middle line:84%
Well, all of their traits
appear here in Sardinia as well,

00:10:36.230 --> 00:10:37.997 align:middle line:84%
and they're remembered
in the place names.

00:10:37.997 --> 00:10:39.830 align:middle line:84%
This is the reason why
no one can understand

00:10:39.830 --> 00:10:41.690 align:middle line:84%
why they're called
places of the giants

00:10:41.690 --> 00:10:44.060 align:middle line:84%
or the burial
places of the jina.

00:10:44.060 --> 00:10:47.610 align:middle line:84%
But those words have a specific
meaning somewhere else,

00:10:47.610 --> 00:10:49.260 align:middle line:84%
and that's how we
unravel the story.

00:10:49.260 --> 00:10:50.635 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And one
of the features

00:10:50.635 --> 00:10:54.170 align:middle line:84%
is that these are very
large-statured people, anywhere

00:10:54.170 --> 00:10:58.820 align:middle line:84%
up to 10, 12, 13 feet tall,
perhaps even a little taller

00:10:58.820 --> 00:11:00.410 align:middle line:90%
here in Sardinia.

00:11:00.410 --> 00:11:02.660 align:middle line:84%
There's a division that
you make here where

00:11:02.660 --> 00:11:04.130 align:middle line:90%
there are the very tall ones.

00:11:04.130 --> 00:11:06.890 align:middle line:84%
Then we start moving
into the giant ones.

00:11:06.890 --> 00:11:09.290 align:middle line:84%
And one of the traits
they have in common

00:11:09.290 --> 00:11:12.320 align:middle line:84%
that you mention in your
book, which really piqued me--

00:11:12.320 --> 00:11:15.350 align:middle line:84%
I was reading your book, and
what had already piqued me here

00:11:15.350 --> 00:11:18.890 align:middle line:84%
doing some research were these
large-statured beings that

00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:20.870 align:middle line:84%
are depicted-- you
can see in Cagliari

00:11:20.870 --> 00:11:22.610 align:middle line:84%
in the museum in
these stone figures

00:11:22.610 --> 00:11:25.610 align:middle line:84%
with these inexplicably
large eyes.

00:11:25.610 --> 00:11:27.770 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, wait a minute.

00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:30.020 align:middle line:84%
Freddy's book is talking
about the same thing.

00:11:30.020 --> 00:11:32.660 align:middle line:84%
They're depicted with these
large eyes everywhere.

00:11:32.660 --> 00:11:34.580 align:middle line:84%
And it occurred
to me that that's

00:11:34.580 --> 00:11:36.800 align:middle line:84%
symbolic for the
ones who can see,

00:11:36.800 --> 00:11:38.140 align:middle line:90%
the ones with sight or vision.

00:11:38.140 --> 00:11:39.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: The awoken one.

00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:39.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:11:39.470 --> 00:11:40.320 align:middle line:90%
And we talked about it.

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:42.230 align:middle line:84%
And you said, that's your
same perception on it.

00:11:42.230 --> 00:11:42.830 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:11:42.830 --> 00:11:44.372 align:middle line:84%
And that goes--
that's actually found

00:11:44.372 --> 00:11:46.010 align:middle line:90%
in the Middle East and Persia.

00:11:46.010 --> 00:11:48.470 align:middle line:84%
It goes back, again,
to the lords of Anu

00:11:48.470 --> 00:11:50.240 align:middle line:90%
who were also the sages.

00:11:50.240 --> 00:11:52.250 align:middle line:84%
And the original
name really means

00:11:52.250 --> 00:11:55.010 align:middle line:84%
an enlightened or awoken
person spiritually

00:11:55.010 --> 00:11:56.780 align:middle line:90%
and also intellectually.

00:11:56.780 --> 00:11:59.240 align:middle line:84%
And the symbol for that
was the eye is wide open.

00:11:59.240 --> 00:12:01.115 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they're
right here in Sardinia.

00:12:01.115 --> 00:12:03.020 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about
some of the other places

00:12:03.020 --> 00:12:06.020 align:middle line:84%
that you research in your
book that had these--

00:12:06.020 --> 00:12:09.610 align:middle line:84%
symbolically the people depicted
in the same way as larger

00:12:09.610 --> 00:12:11.110 align:middle line:90%
than normal with large eyes.

00:12:11.110 --> 00:12:11.910 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:12:11.910 --> 00:12:14.860 align:middle line:84%
I mean, in Edfu, if you look at
one of the panels of the Edfu

00:12:14.860 --> 00:12:17.440 align:middle line:84%
text in the Temple
of Edfu in Egypt,

00:12:17.440 --> 00:12:19.540 align:middle line:84%
they actually give
them an actual height.

00:12:19.540 --> 00:12:21.225 align:middle line:84%
And depending which
qubit you're using,

00:12:21.225 --> 00:12:23.350 align:middle line:84%
because it could be the
royal or the sacred qubit--

00:12:23.350 --> 00:12:24.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Since none of
us know what a qubit is,

00:12:24.790 --> 00:12:26.582 align:middle line:84%
just tell us in feet
and inches, or meters.

00:12:26.582 --> 00:12:28.832 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It basically ends
up at eight and a half feet

00:12:28.832 --> 00:12:29.890 align:middle line:90%
to 10 feet.

00:12:29.890 --> 00:12:32.613 align:middle line:84%
Either way, they're very tall,
which actually synchronizes

00:12:32.613 --> 00:12:34.030 align:middle line:84%
with the size of
the bones that we

00:12:34.030 --> 00:12:35.950 align:middle line:84%
keep finding from
here all the way

00:12:35.950 --> 00:12:38.380 align:middle line:84%
over to Britain in
the giants' graves.

00:12:38.380 --> 00:12:40.390 align:middle line:84%
After that, we get
into giant people,

00:12:40.390 --> 00:12:43.383 align:middle line:84%
and that's where the story
gets a little bit confusing

00:12:43.383 --> 00:12:44.800 align:middle line:84%
because we're
talking about people

00:12:44.800 --> 00:12:46.400 align:middle line:90%
who then interbred with humans.

00:12:46.400 --> 00:12:48.190 align:middle line:84%
They became half-human,
half-divine.

00:12:48.190 --> 00:12:50.560 align:middle line:84%
And it was problematic
at the beginning

00:12:50.560 --> 00:12:53.930 align:middle line:84%
because their DNA apparently
didn't match human DNA.

00:12:53.930 --> 00:12:56.007 align:middle line:84%
It caused all kinds
of abnormalities.

00:12:56.007 --> 00:12:57.715 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things
that came from this

00:12:57.715 --> 00:12:59.860 align:middle line:90%
was a giantess statue.

00:12:59.860 --> 00:13:02.260 align:middle line:84%
And you hear this in
Sardinia, in Southern Europe,

00:13:02.260 --> 00:13:06.402 align:middle line:84%
in India, in Asia, all the
way through Easter Island

00:13:06.402 --> 00:13:07.360 align:middle line:90%
in the Solomon Islands.

00:13:07.360 --> 00:13:08.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And I've recently
heard even in Bolivia,

00:13:08.950 --> 00:13:10.420 align:middle line:90%
although that's not known yet.

00:13:10.420 --> 00:13:12.460 align:middle line:10%
>>SILVA: Yeah, the DNA
tracks all the way back

00:13:12.460 --> 00:13:14.298 align:middle line:10%
to the Black Sea,
oddly enough, which

00:13:14.298 --> 00:13:16.090 align:middle line:10%
is kind of the area,
the general area where

00:13:16.090 --> 00:13:17.745 align:middle line:10%
the Anu used to live.

00:13:17.745 --> 00:13:19.870 align:middle line:84%
So these things are beginning
to converge together.

00:13:19.870 --> 00:13:21.078 align:middle line:90%
They're beginning to overlap.

00:13:21.078 --> 00:13:23.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's what makes the
story kind of compelling

00:13:23.290 --> 00:13:25.390 align:middle line:90%
because there was some kind of--

00:13:25.390 --> 00:13:28.090 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the original sort
of watchers of the Anu

00:13:28.090 --> 00:13:29.950 align:middle line:84%
who were part of the
same group of people,

00:13:29.950 --> 00:13:32.170 align:middle line:84%
they were told not to
intermix with human women

00:13:32.170 --> 00:13:33.940 align:middle line:84%
because there was a
problem with genetics.

00:13:33.940 --> 00:13:37.480 align:middle line:84%
And of all people, the
Wichita of Oklahoma

00:13:37.480 --> 00:13:40.240 align:middle line:84%
still had the story
about saying that when

00:13:40.240 --> 00:13:42.370 align:middle line:84%
the tall people
intermixed with us,

00:13:42.370 --> 00:13:45.640 align:middle line:90%
the women died in childbirth.

00:13:45.640 --> 00:13:48.610 align:middle line:84%
So the babies were born
as the size of infants,

00:13:48.610 --> 00:13:50.140 align:middle line:84%
and that's still
in their memory.

00:13:50.140 --> 00:13:51.950 align:middle line:84%
And the Hopi talk
about this as well.

00:13:51.950 --> 00:13:53.230 align:middle line:90%
So it's not just Sardinia.

00:13:53.230 --> 00:13:54.523 align:middle line:90%
It's also all around the world.

00:13:54.523 --> 00:13:56.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and this
is also in religious texts,

00:13:56.690 --> 00:13:58.330 align:middle line:90%
the talk of giants.

00:13:58.330 --> 00:13:59.650 align:middle line:90%
Even in some--

00:13:59.650 --> 00:14:02.110 align:middle line:84%
I was talking to a girlfriend
before we came here,

00:14:02.110 --> 00:14:04.570 align:middle line:84%
and she said, oh,
that's so interesting.

00:14:04.570 --> 00:14:06.190 align:middle line:84%
She said, in my
son's Sunday school

00:14:06.190 --> 00:14:08.080 align:middle line:84%
they used to teach
that Adam and Eve--

00:14:08.080 --> 00:14:10.090 align:middle line:84%
Adam was 25 feet
tall and Eve was

00:14:10.090 --> 00:14:12.160 align:middle line:90%
23 feet tall in her Christian--

00:14:12.160 --> 00:14:13.735 align:middle line:90%
Christian Sunday school.

00:14:13.735 --> 00:14:14.573 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: [LAUGHS]

00:14:14.573 --> 00:14:16.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: As a matter
of fact, to little five,

00:14:16.490 --> 00:14:17.830 align:middle line:90%
six, seven-year-olds, right?

00:14:17.830 --> 00:14:19.610 align:middle line:84%
And they'll accept
it, no problem.

00:14:19.610 --> 00:14:22.000 align:middle line:84%
But as soon as you become
an adult, you say, no.

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:23.950 align:middle line:84%
I mean, even here
it's so interesting.

00:14:23.950 --> 00:14:27.880 align:middle line:84%
It's, we'll ask the Sardinian
people about the giants.

00:14:27.880 --> 00:14:28.990 align:middle line:90%
We've come for the giants.

00:14:28.990 --> 00:14:29.990 align:middle line:90%
And they're, giants?

00:14:29.990 --> 00:14:30.790 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:14:30.790 --> 00:14:33.490 align:middle line:84%
All the tombs that
say tomba di giganti.

00:14:33.490 --> 00:14:36.020 align:middle line:90%
And they'll say, no giants.

00:14:36.020 --> 00:14:36.820 align:middle line:90%
What giants?

00:14:36.820 --> 00:14:38.860 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And where did the
story come from, I wonder?

00:14:38.860 --> 00:14:40.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the thing is,
it just seems to be obscure.

00:14:40.700 --> 00:14:43.242 align:middle line:84%
It's just accepted that these
are called tombs of the giants,

00:14:43.242 --> 00:14:46.390 align:middle line:84%
and the purpose for them to
have existed to begin with

00:14:46.390 --> 00:14:47.900 align:middle line:90%
has faded away long ago.

00:14:47.900 --> 00:14:48.700 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:14:48.700 --> 00:14:49.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That understanding.

00:14:49.660 --> 00:14:51.790 align:middle line:84%
So that's what we're
trying to bring back here.

00:14:51.790 --> 00:14:52.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:14:52.590 --> 00:14:55.390 align:middle line:84%
And the nuraghe, which is
the towers of the giants.

00:14:55.390 --> 00:14:56.950 align:middle line:84%
And again, you're
kind of baffled

00:14:56.950 --> 00:14:59.080 align:middle line:84%
by why they called it
nuraghe, the Nuragic people.

00:14:59.080 --> 00:15:00.460 align:middle line:84%
We hear about this,
but who were they?

00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:01.520 align:middle line:90%
Where did they come from?

00:15:01.520 --> 00:15:05.080 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was looking at the
origin of words, which is--

00:15:05.080 --> 00:15:07.630 align:middle line:84%
in the old days they
didn't just make up words.

00:15:07.630 --> 00:15:08.810 align:middle line:90%
It meant something.

00:15:08.810 --> 00:15:10.000 align:middle line:90%
It was describing something.

00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:11.958 align:middle line:84%
And I had to go through
all these old languages

00:15:11.958 --> 00:15:13.420 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of
the Mediterranean.

00:15:13.420 --> 00:15:16.670 align:middle line:84%
Libya, Algeria, and
eventually ended up in Malta.

00:15:16.670 --> 00:15:18.550 align:middle line:10%
And the word actually
exists in Malta,

00:15:18.550 --> 00:15:24.160 align:middle line:10%
that nuraghe actually means
a wise or justful person,

00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:25.490 align:middle line:10%
a rightful person.

00:15:25.490 --> 00:15:26.920 align:middle line:90%
In other words, a wisdom keeper.

00:15:26.920 --> 00:15:29.860 align:middle line:84%
So the towers of these
tall people, the giants

00:15:29.860 --> 00:15:33.010 align:middle line:84%
were the towers or the places
where the tall wisdom keepers

00:15:33.010 --> 00:15:33.850 align:middle line:90%
used to live.

00:15:33.850 --> 00:15:35.860 align:middle line:90%
So they were places of assembly.

00:15:35.860 --> 00:15:37.870 align:middle line:84%
Now, that changes the
story considerably

00:15:37.870 --> 00:15:40.390 align:middle line:84%
because we have the
parallel story somewhere

00:15:40.390 --> 00:15:43.960 align:middle line:84%
in Asia Minor with the original
version of the Book of Enoch

00:15:43.960 --> 00:15:46.595 align:middle line:84%
that talks about the
assembly of the Anu, which

00:15:46.595 --> 00:15:48.220 align:middle line:84%
is in these towers
which are all shaped

00:15:48.220 --> 00:15:49.498 align:middle line:90%
like beehives on the inside.

00:15:49.498 --> 00:15:51.790 align:middle line:84%
And you see them all around
the world, the same towers.

00:15:51.790 --> 00:15:53.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're going to take
an amazing tour of these.

00:15:53.650 --> 00:15:55.690 align:middle line:84%
We're taking everybody with
us in a few minutes here.

00:15:55.690 --> 00:15:56.190 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, yeah.

00:15:56.190 --> 00:15:56.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:15:56.570 --> 00:15:57.580 align:middle line:90%
This is the fun part.

00:15:57.580 --> 00:15:58.780 align:middle line:90%
And Luigi-- yes.

00:15:58.780 --> 00:16:00.550 align:middle line:84%
And Luigi's talking
about this as well,

00:16:00.550 --> 00:16:05.350 align:middle line:84%
that in his understanding of
it through his family lineage

00:16:05.350 --> 00:16:09.970 align:middle line:84%
that it these beings who came
and helped assemble the towers.

00:16:09.970 --> 00:16:11.440 align:middle line:84%
And then the
structures that were

00:16:11.440 --> 00:16:14.080 align:middle line:84%
built around them, most
of which have fallen away

00:16:14.080 --> 00:16:16.780 align:middle line:84%
and are just rubble now,
were built for the people

00:16:16.780 --> 00:16:19.090 align:middle line:84%
where the ceremonies
happen inside

00:16:19.090 --> 00:16:20.823 align:middle line:84%
for the builders
of the mountains.

00:16:20.823 --> 00:16:22.990 align:middle line:84%
But there's this twist to
that we'll get to a little

00:16:22.990 --> 00:16:24.340 align:middle line:90%
later as well.

00:16:24.340 --> 00:16:27.400 align:middle line:84%
So now who are you seeing
the builders to be?

00:16:27.400 --> 00:16:30.250 align:middle line:84%
The Shining Ones,
the same ones that

00:16:30.250 --> 00:16:33.070 align:middle line:84%
have come to these various
places around the Earth

00:16:33.070 --> 00:16:35.110 align:middle line:90%
pre-deluge, right?

00:16:35.110 --> 00:16:38.710 align:middle line:84%
Antediluvian times when
let's just stick with the--

00:16:38.710 --> 00:16:42.520 align:middle line:84%
I like the convenience of it,
so let's stick with the Atlantis

00:16:42.520 --> 00:16:44.980 align:middle line:84%
story for a moment
as a starting place

00:16:44.980 --> 00:16:46.450 align:middle line:84%
because we're going
to go all over.

00:16:46.450 --> 00:16:49.900 align:middle line:84%
And it was known in the
day there were people

00:16:49.900 --> 00:16:51.040 align:middle line:90%
that had vision and sight.

00:16:51.040 --> 00:16:53.800 align:middle line:84%
It was known that these
catastrophes were happening

00:16:53.800 --> 00:16:55.210 align:middle line:90%
and were going to be occurring.

00:16:55.210 --> 00:16:56.840 align:middle line:90%
They had foreknowledge of it.

00:16:56.840 --> 00:17:00.610 align:middle line:84%
There were people that were
able to reposition themselves

00:17:00.610 --> 00:17:03.610 align:middle line:84%
to be of service once
this deluge occurred,

00:17:03.610 --> 00:17:07.089 align:middle line:84%
to be able to replant knowledge
into civilization again

00:17:07.089 --> 00:17:09.520 align:middle line:84%
and help raise civilization a
little faster than if people

00:17:09.520 --> 00:17:12.220 align:middle line:84%
were just left struggling
in caves, right?

00:17:12.220 --> 00:17:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And so we have that, and then
we also have survivors, right?

00:17:15.640 --> 00:17:17.569 align:middle line:84%
Living in outposts
around the world.

00:17:17.569 --> 00:17:19.990 align:middle line:84%
So let's say it's a
combination of the two.

00:17:19.990 --> 00:17:22.450 align:middle line:84%
The people of knowledge, are
these the ones that you're

00:17:22.450 --> 00:17:25.040 align:middle line:90%
calling here the nuraghe?

00:17:25.040 --> 00:17:26.230 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Absolutely.

00:17:26.230 --> 00:17:28.095 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, every indication
is that they

00:17:28.095 --> 00:17:30.220 align:middle line:84%
are the same people that
we find in the Middle East

00:17:30.220 --> 00:17:33.130 align:middle line:84%
and also in Easter Island, in
South America, and Yucatan.

00:17:33.130 --> 00:17:34.380 align:middle line:90%
All around the world.

00:17:34.380 --> 00:17:36.190 align:middle line:90%
They have the same methodology.

00:17:36.190 --> 00:17:37.570 align:middle line:90%
They're master astronomers.

00:17:37.570 --> 00:17:39.010 align:middle line:90%
They're great navigators.

00:17:39.010 --> 00:17:40.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mathematicians.

00:17:40.120 --> 00:17:40.570 align:middle line:90%
Yep.

00:17:40.570 --> 00:17:41.570 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Mathematicians.

00:17:41.570 --> 00:17:45.130 align:middle line:84%
They totally understand the laws
of nature, how to bend them.

00:17:45.130 --> 00:17:46.963 align:middle line:84%
You hear this again
and again and again.

00:17:46.963 --> 00:17:48.880 align:middle line:84%
So if people weren't
getting around much back,

00:17:48.880 --> 00:17:51.203 align:middle line:84%
you know, 15,000
years ago, I wonder

00:17:51.203 --> 00:17:53.620 align:middle line:84%
where these stories came from
that are completely similar.

00:17:53.620 --> 00:17:55.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
sophisticated-- yes,

00:17:55.330 --> 00:17:57.430 align:middle line:84%
and sophisticated
agricultural practices,

00:17:57.430 --> 00:17:59.292 align:middle line:84%
which were necessary
to rebuild cultures.

00:17:59.292 --> 00:18:01.000 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And suddenly
from that point on,

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:03.208 align:middle line:84%
where were these people that
appear in the narrative?

00:18:03.208 --> 00:18:04.600 align:middle line:84%
And the Mesopotamian
narrative is

00:18:04.600 --> 00:18:06.280 align:middle line:84%
where we get most of
the information from,

00:18:06.280 --> 00:18:08.710 align:middle line:84%
which is the narrative that
the Sumerians borrowed that was

00:18:08.710 --> 00:18:09.910 align:middle line:90%
borrowed by the Babylonians--

00:18:09.910 --> 00:18:11.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's where
everything keeps get hung--

00:18:11.350 --> 00:18:12.558 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: The biblical people.

00:18:12.558 --> 00:18:14.290 align:middle line:84%
And then you get
confused by dogma.

00:18:14.290 --> 00:18:16.900 align:middle line:84%
But if you go back to
the origin of things,

00:18:16.900 --> 00:18:19.690 align:middle line:84%
they talk about there was a
civilization that ran parallel

00:18:19.690 --> 00:18:23.530 align:middle line:84%
with hunter gatherers, and
it was they who drip feed

00:18:23.530 --> 00:18:27.130 align:middle line:84%
knowledge to the humans
in a way that doesn't--

00:18:27.130 --> 00:18:29.620 align:middle line:84%
it's sort of concurrent with
their level of understanding,

00:18:29.620 --> 00:18:31.840 align:middle line:84%
because if you give
advanced knowledge to people

00:18:31.840 --> 00:18:34.870 align:middle line:84%
who were working on a
rudimentary basis, what happens

00:18:34.870 --> 00:18:37.660 align:middle line:84%
is that when you have ignorance
with advanced knowledge,

00:18:37.660 --> 00:18:40.030 align:middle line:84%
the two make very
strange bedfellows.

00:18:40.030 --> 00:18:41.110 align:middle line:90%
Things can go very wrong.

00:18:41.110 --> 00:18:43.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Information is
bastardized really quickly.

00:18:43.060 --> 00:18:43.480 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:18:43.480 --> 00:18:43.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:18:43.600 --> 00:18:44.260 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And that's
what happened.

00:18:44.260 --> 00:18:46.300 align:middle line:84%
This is why the watchers
and the Anunnaki

00:18:46.300 --> 00:18:49.840 align:middle line:84%
gets a really bad name, but
that's not how the story was.

00:18:49.840 --> 00:18:51.127 align:middle line:90%
These people were teachers.

00:18:51.127 --> 00:18:52.960 align:middle line:84%
They were slow-- they
were looking at humans

00:18:52.960 --> 00:18:54.340 align:middle line:84%
and they're saying,
well, we want

00:18:54.340 --> 00:18:57.020 align:middle line:84%
to stay away from them because
we know much more than they do,

00:18:57.020 --> 00:18:58.490 align:middle line:84%
which is a whole
story in itself.

00:18:58.490 --> 00:19:01.690 align:middle line:84%
But once in a while they would
say, go down and just teach

00:19:01.690 --> 00:19:04.130 align:middle line:84%
them how to grow crop,
domesticate wheat or something

00:19:04.130 --> 00:19:05.380 align:middle line:90%
like that, and then come back.

00:19:05.380 --> 00:19:07.990 align:middle line:84%
Just feed that into them
and see where that goes.

00:19:07.990 --> 00:19:09.460 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
we start getting

00:19:09.460 --> 00:19:12.790 align:middle line:84%
the story of the civilization of
humanity from hunter gatherers

00:19:12.790 --> 00:19:15.520 align:middle line:84%
into people who were
creating communities.

00:19:15.520 --> 00:19:17.523 align:middle line:84%
It happened suddenly
all around the world.

00:19:17.523 --> 00:19:19.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and it has
been depicted artistically

00:19:19.690 --> 00:19:20.490 align:middle line:90%
in the novels.

00:19:20.490 --> 00:19:22.180 align:middle line:10%
For example, "Clan
of the Cave Bears."

00:19:22.180 --> 00:19:25.300 align:middle line:10%
We're talking about the
concurrent existence

00:19:25.300 --> 00:19:27.880 align:middle line:10%
of these two cultures, very
diverse cultures in terms

00:19:27.880 --> 00:19:29.110 align:middle line:10%
of knowledge and influence.

00:19:29.110 --> 00:19:30.710 align:middle line:84%
Nordic-looking, you
would say, right?

00:19:30.710 --> 00:19:31.510 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Caucasian.

00:19:31.510 --> 00:19:32.095 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, Caucasian.

00:19:32.095 --> 00:19:34.040 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Which looks a
bit weird in Polynesia.

00:19:34.040 --> 00:19:34.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It does.

00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:37.420 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is
in your book, all

00:19:37.420 --> 00:19:40.450 align:middle line:84%
of these-- in all of
these naval civilizations

00:19:40.450 --> 00:19:43.540 align:middle line:84%
where humanity was
reseeded with knowledge,

00:19:43.540 --> 00:19:45.610 align:middle line:84%
the beings that
show up are tall.

00:19:45.610 --> 00:19:47.410 align:middle line:90%
Not only do they have big eyes.

00:19:47.410 --> 00:19:48.620 align:middle line:90%
They're fair-skinned.

00:19:48.620 --> 00:19:49.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yes.

00:19:49.420 --> 00:19:49.600 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:19:49.600 --> 00:19:50.400 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:19:50.400 --> 00:19:53.200 align:middle line:84%
And the hair is normally
from blond to auburn

00:19:53.200 --> 00:19:55.045 align:middle line:90%
and a phase of red in between.

00:19:55.045 --> 00:19:56.545 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: A lot of
red hair in there.

00:19:56.545 --> 00:19:57.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and
you also said--

00:19:57.370 --> 00:19:57.910 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Green eyes, blue eyes.

00:19:57.910 --> 00:20:00.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Green and
blue eyes, pale eyes.

00:20:00.370 --> 00:20:05.140 align:middle line:84%
Now how does this match up
with the Anu, for example?

00:20:05.140 --> 00:20:08.410 align:middle line:84%
How does that match up
with the Atlantean beings

00:20:08.410 --> 00:20:09.813 align:middle line:90%
that we're talking about?

00:20:09.813 --> 00:20:11.980 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It matches up
perfectly because if you go--

00:20:11.980 --> 00:20:14.480 align:middle line:84%
one of the things I like doing
is traveling around the world

00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:17.847 align:middle line:84%
to strange places and asking
local people, what do you know?

00:20:17.847 --> 00:20:19.180 align:middle line:90%
What did your parents teach you?

00:20:19.180 --> 00:20:20.290 align:middle line:84%
What did your
grandparents teach you?

00:20:20.290 --> 00:20:22.390 align:middle line:84%
And what did your
predecessors write about?

00:20:22.390 --> 00:20:23.860 align:middle line:90%
And the stories all line up.

00:20:23.860 --> 00:20:24.850 align:middle line:90%
They all overlap.

00:20:24.850 --> 00:20:26.350 align:middle line:84%
And there are always
tall people who

00:20:26.350 --> 00:20:27.850 align:middle line:84%
were sages, who
were astronomers,

00:20:27.850 --> 00:20:30.650 align:middle line:84%
who got around flying
through the air almost.

00:20:30.650 --> 00:20:31.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:20:31.450 --> 00:20:32.950 align:middle line:90%
Ships with no oars.

00:20:32.950 --> 00:20:34.930 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Ships with no
oars and flying shields.

00:20:34.930 --> 00:20:35.740 align:middle line:90%
I'm thinking, hmm.

00:20:35.740 --> 00:20:39.280 align:middle line:10%
Someone knew about anti-gravity
and the rocks moving

00:20:39.280 --> 00:20:42.820 align:middle line:10%
to build the temples overnight
to the voice of a command

00:20:42.820 --> 00:20:44.858 align:middle line:10%
or a tone from a trumpet.

00:20:44.858 --> 00:20:46.150 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Acoustic frequencies.

00:20:46.150 --> 00:20:46.450 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:20:46.450 --> 00:20:47.820 align:middle line:90%
So these are the same people.

00:20:47.820 --> 00:20:49.540 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I'm fascinated
about the whole story,

00:20:49.540 --> 00:20:51.820 align:middle line:84%
that we're not talking
about individual portions

00:20:51.820 --> 00:20:53.120 align:middle line:90%
of civilization.

00:20:53.120 --> 00:20:54.940 align:middle line:84%
Every culture on the
face of the Earth

00:20:54.940 --> 00:20:57.610 align:middle line:84%
talks about having a
parallel civilization,

00:20:57.610 --> 00:20:59.260 align:middle line:84%
and they weren't
unnerved by them.

00:20:59.260 --> 00:21:03.222 align:middle line:84%
They said they were human-like,
but they're not quite human.

00:21:03.222 --> 00:21:04.930 align:middle line:84%
And they weren't alien
either apparently,

00:21:04.930 --> 00:21:07.447 align:middle line:84%
because otherwise they
would have come up and said,

00:21:07.447 --> 00:21:09.280 align:middle line:84%
well, we feel very
unnerved by these people.

00:21:09.280 --> 00:21:10.080 align:middle line:90%
But no.

00:21:10.080 --> 00:21:12.680 align:middle line:84%
All of these storytellers
who are humans,

00:21:12.680 --> 00:21:14.230 align:middle line:90%
they were not unnerved by them.

00:21:14.230 --> 00:21:16.248 align:middle line:84%
They just said that they
didn't look like us.

00:21:16.248 --> 00:21:18.790 align:middle line:84%
And one of the reasons that they
call them the Shining People

00:21:18.790 --> 00:21:20.248 align:middle line:84%
or the Shining Ones
is because they

00:21:20.248 --> 00:21:22.570 align:middle line:84%
had to keep smearing
this oil on their skin

00:21:22.570 --> 00:21:24.250 align:middle line:84%
as though they
felt uncomfortable

00:21:24.250 --> 00:21:25.895 align:middle line:84%
being here on Earth
with the sunlight.

00:21:25.895 --> 00:21:27.520 align:middle line:84%
There was something
unusual about that,

00:21:27.520 --> 00:21:29.200 align:middle line:90%
and that stuck with me.

00:21:29.200 --> 00:21:32.230 align:middle line:84%
And also the fact that they had
this wonderful smell of myrrh

00:21:32.230 --> 00:21:33.310 align:middle line:90%
about them.

00:21:33.310 --> 00:21:34.900 align:middle line:90%
They dressed in long tunics.

00:21:34.900 --> 00:21:37.630 align:middle line:84%
And you get the same
story in Central America

00:21:37.630 --> 00:21:40.130 align:middle line:84%
and South America as you would
do here in the Mediterranean.

00:21:40.130 --> 00:21:42.370 align:middle line:84%
So that's what got my
attention, that we're

00:21:42.370 --> 00:21:44.800 align:middle line:84%
talking about the
same people stretched

00:21:44.800 --> 00:21:47.970 align:middle line:84%
around the world in specific
and strategic locations

00:21:47.970 --> 00:21:48.770 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:21:48.770 --> 00:21:52.630 align:middle line:84%
It was from there that we get
the stories of the one sage

00:21:52.630 --> 00:21:56.350 align:middle line:84%
with the seven groups of
Shining People, the seven sages.

00:21:56.350 --> 00:21:58.298 align:middle line:84%
There was always a
charismatic leader.

00:21:58.298 --> 00:22:00.340 align:middle line:84%
And this person would have
seven people with them

00:22:00.340 --> 00:22:02.950 align:middle line:84%
who knew one facet of
the knowledge of things.

00:22:02.950 --> 00:22:06.100 align:middle line:84%
One of them was the woman, but
she has all the information.

00:22:06.100 --> 00:22:08.438 align:middle line:84%
She was the one to
go to for all the--

00:22:08.438 --> 00:22:09.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: She was the database.

00:22:09.730 --> 00:22:12.040 align:middle line:90%
She consolidated it all.

