That's where the word
fairy comes from.

00:23:50.730 --> 00:23:53.610 align:middle line:84%
Yes, it is a supernatural
being in one-- an elemental

00:23:53.610 --> 00:23:55.300 align:middle line:90%
being in one culture.

00:23:55.300 --> 00:23:58.620 align:middle line:84%
But originally, it was
related to the fae people,

00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:01.070 align:middle line:84%
the wisdom keepers of a
very, very long lineage

00:24:01.070 --> 00:24:02.570 align:middle line:84%
said to be older
than the Egyptians.

00:24:02.570 --> 00:24:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And this is where we get
to learn about the Anu

00:24:05.040 --> 00:24:07.890 align:middle line:84%
and the Anunnaki, the
wisdom keepers who became

00:24:07.890 --> 00:24:10.440 align:middle line:84%
called the Apkallu, which
literally means sage.

00:24:10.440 --> 00:24:13.590 align:middle line:84%
And they were said to have
governed from places like this.

00:24:13.590 --> 00:24:16.830 align:middle line:84%
They described these
fairy rings where there

00:24:16.830 --> 00:24:19.200 align:middle line:90%
were nine keepers of the ring.

00:24:19.200 --> 00:24:20.310 align:middle line:90%
One of them was a woman.

00:24:20.310 --> 00:24:23.190 align:middle line:84%
And they were all presided
by one central lord,

00:24:23.190 --> 00:24:25.350 align:middle line:84%
and they basically took
charge of all the portions

00:24:25.350 --> 00:24:26.220 align:middle line:90%
of the Earth.

00:24:26.220 --> 00:24:27.430 align:middle line:90%
And they said they were--

00:24:27.430 --> 00:24:29.880 align:middle line:84%
met in councils into
towers just like this

00:24:29.880 --> 00:24:32.940 align:middle line:84%
that had the beehive shape
in the inside, which it does.

00:24:32.940 --> 00:24:34.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow.

00:24:34.090 --> 00:24:34.890 align:middle line:90%
That's amazing.

00:24:34.890 --> 00:24:37.560 align:middle line:90%


00:24:37.560 --> 00:24:39.540 align:middle line:90%
This is a beehive.

00:24:39.540 --> 00:24:40.950 align:middle line:90%
It looks like, what?

00:24:40.950 --> 00:24:43.500 align:middle line:90%
About 15 feet high?

00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:44.640 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: A little bit more.

00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:48.130 align:middle line:84%
So we're inside an actual
island, if you'd like.

00:24:48.130 --> 00:24:50.047 align:middle line:84%
And here, this is
completely out of alignment.

00:24:50.047 --> 00:24:52.463 align:middle line:84%
You think, well, if they were
clever enough to build this,

00:24:52.463 --> 00:24:53.400 align:middle line:90%
why not build it here?

00:24:53.400 --> 00:24:56.580 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you stand here and you
just scratch down a little bit,

00:24:56.580 --> 00:24:58.680 align:middle line:84%
it narrows the gap
between the walls,

00:24:58.680 --> 00:25:02.190 align:middle line:84%
so it's aligning to the
actual solstice sunrise

00:25:02.190 --> 00:25:05.970 align:middle line:84%
as it appears through
this gap in 6,000 BC.

00:25:05.970 --> 00:25:09.180 align:middle line:84%
It's the one time the
things just line up.

00:25:09.180 --> 00:25:11.970 align:middle line:84%
And that, again, puts us
back into the time frame

00:25:11.970 --> 00:25:14.070 align:middle line:84%
of these wisdom
keepers, and we go back

00:25:14.070 --> 00:25:17.580 align:middle line:84%
to the idea of why this place is
called the nuraghe, the towers

00:25:17.580 --> 00:25:18.413 align:middle line:90%
of the giants.

00:25:18.413 --> 00:25:21.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you look at the
etymology of the word, which

00:25:21.210 --> 00:25:25.590 align:middle line:84%
you can find in Malta, it means
the just or rightful people.

00:25:25.590 --> 00:25:27.750 align:middle line:84%
And that was usually
the idea that there

00:25:27.750 --> 00:25:29.550 align:middle line:84%
was some group of
wisdom keepers that

00:25:29.550 --> 00:25:32.910 align:middle line:84%
knew all about the knowledge
about the stars, navigation,

00:25:32.910 --> 00:25:35.215 align:middle line:84%
mathematics, how to
bend the laws of nature.

00:25:35.215 --> 00:25:37.090 align:middle line:84%
And you hear this story
all around the world.

00:25:37.090 --> 00:25:38.280 align:middle line:90%
It's not unique to Sardinia.

00:25:38.280 --> 00:25:39.680 align:middle line:90%
It's just covered everywhere.

00:25:39.680 --> 00:25:41.430 align:middle line:84%
And these were the
places where they would

00:25:41.430 --> 00:25:43.320 align:middle line:90%
meet and have their counsel.

00:25:43.320 --> 00:25:45.060 align:middle line:84%
But they're also
places where they also

00:25:45.060 --> 00:25:47.670 align:middle line:90%
conduct secret affairs.

00:25:47.670 --> 00:25:51.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think it's important
to really point out here

00:25:51.720 --> 00:25:54.660 align:middle line:84%
that energetically, whether
it's our remote viewers,

00:25:54.660 --> 00:25:57.870 align:middle line:84%
whether it's each one of
us individually, each time

00:25:57.870 --> 00:26:00.330 align:middle line:84%
we tap into one of
these places, we

00:26:00.330 --> 00:26:02.820 align:middle line:84%
could be tapping into
any point in history.

00:26:02.820 --> 00:26:04.440 align:middle line:84%
And often, it's
the one that has,

00:26:04.440 --> 00:26:07.770 align:middle line:84%
as we talked about off
camera, the most dense emotion

00:26:07.770 --> 00:26:11.830 align:middle line:84%
or the most recent traumatic
or dense experience.

00:26:11.830 --> 00:26:14.040 align:middle line:84%
So we don't know
historically what time we're

00:26:14.040 --> 00:26:15.690 align:middle line:84%
tapping into in
terms of the feeling,

00:26:15.690 --> 00:26:17.550 align:middle line:84%
but they have very
distinct feelings.

00:26:17.550 --> 00:26:19.380 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times,
we're all picking up

00:26:19.380 --> 00:26:21.103 align:middle line:90%
a similar feeling in the cave.

00:26:21.103 --> 00:26:22.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And you
expect that from things

00:26:22.770 --> 00:26:24.970 align:middle line:84%
that have been built
for thousands of years.

00:26:24.970 --> 00:26:27.360 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they go from being
used as sacred places

00:26:27.360 --> 00:26:29.565 align:middle line:84%
to places of
assembly to hospitals

00:26:29.565 --> 00:26:33.300 align:middle line:84%
to a place of corralling
people during times of war.

00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:35.520 align:middle line:84%
And you see the nuraghe
being expanded outwards

00:26:35.520 --> 00:26:36.660 align:middle line:90%
from a central tower.

00:26:36.660 --> 00:26:38.670 align:middle line:84%
You can see the
development of the building

00:26:38.670 --> 00:26:40.860 align:middle line:84%
relative to the time and
the purpose for which it

00:26:40.860 --> 00:26:42.520 align:middle line:90%
was needed in those times.

00:26:42.520 --> 00:26:44.442 align:middle line:84%
And that's where we get
the story so confused,

00:26:44.442 --> 00:26:45.900 align:middle line:84%
and that's where
archaeology starts

00:26:45.900 --> 00:26:47.817 align:middle line:84%
getting very confused
because they accept this

00:26:47.817 --> 00:26:50.160 align:middle line:84%
as being designed as a whole
right from the beginning.

00:26:50.160 --> 00:26:51.600 align:middle line:84%
But there's no
development stage.

00:26:51.600 --> 00:26:52.975 align:middle line:84%
You have to start
with something.

00:26:52.975 --> 00:26:53.775 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:26:53.775 --> 00:26:55.990 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes these are
built on older nuraghe too.

00:26:55.990 --> 00:26:56.310 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

00:26:56.310 --> 00:26:57.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We have
to remember that.

00:26:57.270 --> 00:26:57.600 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Absolutely.

00:26:57.600 --> 00:26:59.183 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you've
pointed this out,

00:26:59.183 --> 00:27:01.750 align:middle line:84%
that the older parts
of these structures,

00:27:01.750 --> 00:27:05.220 align:middle line:84%
meaning there's more
underneath in a lot of cases,

00:27:05.220 --> 00:27:08.940 align:middle line:84%
the older they are, the
more refined and the larger

00:27:08.940 --> 00:27:11.490 align:middle line:84%
the stones are, meaning
the higher the civilization

00:27:11.490 --> 00:27:12.458 align:middle line:90%
and capability, right?

00:27:12.458 --> 00:27:15.000 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Which were completely
opposite to what civilizations

00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:15.880 align:middle line:90%
are supposed to do.

00:27:15.880 --> 00:27:18.120 align:middle line:84%
You're supposed to start
off with rudimentary tools,

00:27:18.120 --> 00:27:20.160 align:middle line:84%
and then you go big
and you get really

00:27:20.160 --> 00:27:21.810 align:middle line:90%
precise and mathematical.

00:27:21.810 --> 00:27:23.160 align:middle line:90%
And here we start backwards.

00:27:23.160 --> 00:27:27.090 align:middle line:84%
We start up with major masonry,
really megalithic masonry,

00:27:27.090 --> 00:27:28.200 align:middle line:90%
beautifully fitted.

00:27:28.200 --> 00:27:32.340 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely aligned to the
stars, to its placement

00:27:32.340 --> 00:27:35.490 align:middle line:84%
on the landscape and its
positioning on the Earth's

00:27:35.490 --> 00:27:36.690 align:middle line:90%
telluric currents as well.

00:27:36.690 --> 00:27:38.790 align:middle line:84%
Each one of these
places, they sense

00:27:38.790 --> 00:27:41.260 align:middle line:84%
that the Earth has
its own web of energy,

00:27:41.260 --> 00:27:44.120 align:middle line:84%
which we can now use very
expensive equipment to measure.

00:27:44.120 --> 00:27:46.620 align:middle line:84%
If you don't have the money,
you can have dowsing equipment.

00:27:46.620 --> 00:27:48.660 align:middle line:84%
The two come up
with the same thing.

00:27:48.660 --> 00:27:52.720 align:middle line:84%
But they start from a very high
educational and intellectual

00:27:52.720 --> 00:27:53.520 align:middle line:90%
point.

00:27:53.520 --> 00:27:54.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The earliest people.

00:27:54.070 --> 00:27:55.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it gets
worse as it gets older.

00:27:55.770 --> 00:27:57.645 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or you can
say we've evolved a bit.

00:27:57.645 --> 00:27:59.880 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yes.

00:27:59.880 --> 00:28:02.220 align:middle line:84%
And these places appear
to suddenly arrive

00:28:02.220 --> 00:28:03.150 align:middle line:90%
without any precedent.

00:28:03.150 --> 00:28:06.300 align:middle line:84%
They didn't just build
huts and develop into this.

00:28:06.300 --> 00:28:07.682 align:middle line:90%
Just appeared by itself.

00:28:07.682 --> 00:28:09.390 align:middle line:84%
So it must have come
from a foreknowledge

00:28:09.390 --> 00:28:11.800 align:middle line:84%
of something else that was
already a set of precedents.

00:28:11.800 --> 00:28:12.675 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:28:12.675 --> 00:28:15.507 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it basically
went downhill from there,

00:28:15.507 --> 00:28:17.340 align:middle line:84%
because if you look
outside of this building

00:28:17.340 --> 00:28:18.810 align:middle line:90%
and many others in Sardinia.

00:28:18.810 --> 00:28:21.030 align:middle line:84%
It's clear that they
were built on-- again

00:28:21.030 --> 00:28:23.500 align:middle line:84%
and again, they were
reused for other purposes,

00:28:23.500 --> 00:28:25.390 align:middle line:84%
but the construction
gets worse over time.

00:28:25.390 --> 00:28:25.530 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:28:25.530 --> 00:28:26.010 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:28:26.010 --> 00:28:27.900 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: The stones get
smaller and sloppier.

00:28:27.900 --> 00:28:28.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:28:28.700 --> 00:28:30.347 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So how
about this coiled

00:28:30.347 --> 00:28:32.430 align:middle line:84%
serpent that goes around
this chamber, all the way

00:28:32.430 --> 00:28:33.310 align:middle line:90%
to the top?

00:28:33.310 --> 00:28:35.310 align:middle line:84%
There's a word for
that in Mesopotamia.

00:28:35.310 --> 00:28:38.280 align:middle line:84%
It's called sumer, which is
where Sumerian comes from,

00:28:38.280 --> 00:28:39.830 align:middle line:90%
which means coiled serpent.

00:28:39.830 --> 00:28:42.500 align:middle line:84%
And the nickname of these
people, these wisdom keepers,

00:28:42.500 --> 00:28:44.730 align:middle line:90%
was the people of the serpent.

00:28:44.730 --> 00:28:45.530 align:middle line:90%
So now we know.

00:28:45.530 --> 00:28:47.420 align:middle line:84%
We have a correlation
between a word,

00:28:47.420 --> 00:28:49.730 align:middle line:84%
a structural foundation
of a building,

00:28:49.730 --> 00:28:53.010 align:middle line:84%
and the purpose for
which it was used.

00:28:53.010 --> 00:28:55.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: God,
this is beautiful.

00:28:55.650 --> 00:28:56.575 align:middle line:90%
Ha!

00:28:56.575 --> 00:28:57.375 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Wow.

00:28:57.375 --> 00:28:59.950 align:middle line:90%


00:28:59.950 --> 00:29:01.600 align:middle line:90%
So you look at the landscape.

00:29:01.600 --> 00:29:03.535 align:middle line:84%
It's a completely
designed landscape.

00:29:03.535 --> 00:29:06.710 align:middle line:84%
There are artificially flattened
mountains all the way around.

00:29:06.710 --> 00:29:11.545 align:middle line:84%
So if you were here in 6000 BC
after the sun has gone down,

00:29:11.545 --> 00:29:15.400 align:middle line:84%
Orion suddenly appears
above this flattened area

00:29:15.400 --> 00:29:17.340 align:middle line:90%
in the sky, followed shortly--

00:29:17.340 --> 00:29:19.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So are you saying
they shaved the mountains so you

00:29:19.840 --> 00:29:20.987 align:middle line:90%
could see Orion properly?

00:29:20.987 --> 00:29:22.570 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: You see the
actual alignment.

00:29:22.570 --> 00:29:23.290 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I see.

00:29:23.290 --> 00:29:25.165 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So it must been
an incredible sight,

00:29:25.165 --> 00:29:28.945 align:middle line:84%
watching this incredible
display of Sirius chasing Orion

00:29:28.945 --> 00:29:30.200 align:middle line:90%
through the night.

00:29:30.200 --> 00:29:31.173 align:middle line:90%
So it's a lot of work.

00:29:31.173 --> 00:29:32.590 align:middle line:84%
They're obviously
great romantics.

00:29:32.590 --> 00:29:33.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A lot of thought.

00:29:33.640 --> 00:29:34.480 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:29:34.480 --> 00:29:36.700 align:middle line:84%
All to have this wonderful
sense of connection

00:29:36.700 --> 00:29:38.997 align:middle line:84%
to what they call the homeland,
the original homeland.

00:29:38.997 --> 00:29:41.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So tell me what
was most striking to you

00:29:41.080 --> 00:29:42.760 align:middle line:90%
about Ruju.

00:29:42.760 --> 00:29:44.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Ruju was extraordinary.

00:29:44.140 --> 00:29:47.845 align:middle line:84%
It was like it was left
alone in its essence.

00:29:47.845 --> 00:29:49.100 align:middle line:90%
You just walk in.

00:29:49.100 --> 00:29:51.100 align:middle line:84%
And I think even the
camera crew picked this up.

00:29:51.100 --> 00:29:52.900 align:middle line:84%
And you just walk in
and you feel a sense

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:55.930 align:middle line:84%
that there's something
very coherent about it.

00:29:55.930 --> 00:29:58.030 align:middle line:84%
There's an intellectual
coherence, but also

00:29:58.030 --> 00:30:00.060 align:middle line:90%
a sense of power.

00:30:00.060 --> 00:30:01.400 align:middle line:90%
A subtle power.

00:30:01.400 --> 00:30:02.710 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't have to show it off.

00:30:02.710 --> 00:30:04.720 align:middle line:90%
It just is what it is.

00:30:04.720 --> 00:30:07.420 align:middle line:84%
It's a sense of
connection to everything.

00:30:07.420 --> 00:30:10.105 align:middle line:84%
It says that you can go
in there and see clearly.

00:30:10.105 --> 00:30:11.980 align:middle line:84%
It's hard to explain
when you're actually not

00:30:11.980 --> 00:30:15.648 align:middle line:84%
there because you're trying to
take a feeling of a landscape

00:30:15.648 --> 00:30:17.440 align:middle line:84%
where you suddenly have
a clear vision of--

00:30:17.440 --> 00:30:19.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, the geometry
and the energy inside

00:30:19.600 --> 00:30:21.340 align:middle line:84%
and the building
materials, the granite,

00:30:21.340 --> 00:30:24.520 align:middle line:84%
the silicon embedded in
the granite, all of this

00:30:24.520 --> 00:30:26.583 align:middle line:84%
is conducive to clear
states of consciousness.

00:30:26.583 --> 00:30:28.375 align:middle line:84%
But that's why it was
built the way it was.

00:30:28.375 --> 00:30:30.730 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It's designed
to musical notation.

00:30:30.730 --> 00:30:34.390 align:middle line:84%
The shape and the height ratios
give you a certain relationship

00:30:34.390 --> 00:30:36.910 align:middle line:84%
to the energy of place,
and that contributes also

00:30:36.910 --> 00:30:39.640 align:middle line:84%
to the feel that you go
in there as a tuning fork.

00:30:39.640 --> 00:30:41.410 align:middle line:84%
You're inside the
big tuning fork.

00:30:41.410 --> 00:30:44.140 align:middle line:84%
And only a small difference
between a few meters

00:30:44.140 --> 00:30:46.740 align:middle line:84%
between here and there will
create a completely different

00:30:46.740 --> 00:30:47.540 align:middle line:90%
feeling.

00:30:47.540 --> 00:30:49.450 align:middle line:84%
The Russians had figured
this out years ago

00:30:49.450 --> 00:30:51.200 align:middle line:84%
when they were looking
at this mumbo jumbo

00:30:51.200 --> 00:30:52.990 align:middle line:84%
and they said, well,
if we build buildings

00:30:52.990 --> 00:30:55.000 align:middle line:84%
in the same manner
as these old places,

00:30:55.000 --> 00:30:56.590 align:middle line:84%
surely they can
influence people now.

00:30:56.590 --> 00:30:57.923 align:middle line:90%
And they found actually it does.

00:30:57.923 --> 00:31:00.280 align:middle line:84%
The shape of place
has a definite effect

00:31:00.280 --> 00:31:01.490 align:middle line:90%
on your sense of being.

00:31:01.490 --> 00:31:04.000 align:middle line:84%
Which also comes to--
brings us to the point of,

00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:05.140 align:middle line:90%
why these rocks?

00:31:05.140 --> 00:31:06.860 align:middle line:84%
Because there was a
lot of local stone,

00:31:06.860 --> 00:31:09.100 align:middle line:84%
but they went a long
way to get volcanic rock

00:31:09.100 --> 00:31:10.010 align:middle line:90%
to build the nuraghe.

00:31:10.010 --> 00:31:11.080 align:middle line:90%
That's a lot of work.

00:31:11.080 --> 00:31:13.342 align:middle line:84%
Then you have to shave
this really awkward stone.

00:31:13.342 --> 00:31:14.800 align:middle line:84%
Well, that has a
lot of iron in it.

00:31:14.800 --> 00:31:15.790 align:middle line:90%
It has magnetite in it.

00:31:15.790 --> 00:31:17.020 align:middle line:90%
It has a crystal in it.

00:31:17.020 --> 00:31:20.800 align:middle line:84%
You put this together, it
creates a big energy edifice.

00:31:20.800 --> 00:31:23.080 align:middle line:84%
A piezoelectric effect
is taking place.

00:31:23.080 --> 00:31:26.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It seemed like it was
all granite and volcanic rock.

00:31:26.200 --> 00:31:27.460 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: In Ruju, absolutely.

00:31:27.460 --> 00:31:28.260 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:31:28.260 --> 00:31:31.040 align:middle line:84%
And that has its own power, and
it's retained within itself.

00:31:31.040 --> 00:31:34.562 align:middle line:84%
So when you go in and interact
with it, your spirit of place

00:31:34.562 --> 00:31:36.520 align:middle line:84%
and your spirit of mind,
the two meld together,

00:31:36.520 --> 00:31:37.600 align:middle line:90%
and you're somewhere else.

00:31:37.600 --> 00:31:38.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:31:38.020 --> 00:31:38.820 align:middle line:90%
The age again.

00:31:38.820 --> 00:31:42.130 align:middle line:84%
Recap the age of Ruju,
according to your alignments.

00:31:42.130 --> 00:31:45.160 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Ah, this is where
we get into pottery shards.

00:31:45.160 --> 00:31:46.880 align:middle line:84%
And the pottery shard
people will say,

00:31:46.880 --> 00:31:50.110 align:middle line:84%
well, we went to the deep layer
of dirt in the sacred site

00:31:50.110 --> 00:31:51.760 align:middle line:84%
and we found pottery
shards and bones.

00:31:51.760 --> 00:31:52.630 align:middle line:90%
We can date those.

00:31:52.630 --> 00:31:54.580 align:middle line:84%
That's when the
site was built. No.

00:31:54.580 --> 00:31:57.100 align:middle line:84%
If you're going to go
and do stuff like this

00:31:57.100 --> 00:31:58.930 align:middle line:84%
and take the time and
the effort to build

00:31:58.930 --> 00:32:01.210 align:middle line:84%
these incredible
monuments, you're

00:32:01.210 --> 00:32:04.040 align:middle line:84%
not going to let dirt and
broken pottery stay in there.

00:32:04.040 --> 00:32:07.060 align:middle line:84%
This tells me the time when
the site was decommissioned

00:32:07.060 --> 00:32:08.830 align:middle line:90%
and dirt starts building up.

00:32:08.830 --> 00:32:10.375 align:middle line:90%
People will take shelters.

00:32:10.375 --> 00:32:13.630 align:middle line:84%
They break a pot by accident,
and that's what they're dating.

00:32:13.630 --> 00:32:17.080 align:middle line:84%
And they'll say, well, we agree
with some of the astronomers

00:32:17.080 --> 00:32:19.900 align:middle line:84%
that, yes, the sites were
astronomically significant.

00:32:19.900 --> 00:32:23.260 align:middle line:84%
And usually it's the alignment
of the doorways, the position

00:32:23.260 --> 00:32:24.400 align:middle line:90%
of what it was looking at.

00:32:24.400 --> 00:32:26.650 align:middle line:84%
And they'll say,
yes, we agree that it

00:32:26.650 --> 00:32:29.440 align:middle line:84%
was looking at the winter
solstice sunset or the sunrise

00:32:29.440 --> 00:32:32.290 align:middle line:90%
or the equinox 3,500 years ago.

00:32:32.290 --> 00:32:34.240 align:middle line:84%
And you say, OK,
we'll accept that.

00:32:34.240 --> 00:32:36.580 align:middle line:84%
But now we have the
technology and the mathematics

00:32:36.580 --> 00:32:38.350 align:middle line:84%
to be able to
project back in time

00:32:38.350 --> 00:32:39.833 align:middle line:90%
at any given spot on Earth.

00:32:39.833 --> 00:32:42.250 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at this on the
computer and I'm going, no.

00:32:42.250 --> 00:32:44.920 align:middle line:84%
The sun 3,000 years
ago was over here.

00:32:44.920 --> 00:32:46.510 align:middle line:84%
Once you start
going back this way

00:32:46.510 --> 00:32:49.060 align:middle line:84%
and you start
recalibrating the heavens,

00:32:49.060 --> 00:32:51.610 align:middle line:84%
because the Earth shifts
relative to its background

00:32:51.610 --> 00:32:55.960 align:middle line:84%
of stars, one degree every
72 years, things misaligned.

00:32:55.960 --> 00:32:58.960 align:middle line:84%
When we get to 6,000 BC
on the winter solstice,

00:32:58.960 --> 00:33:01.450 align:middle line:84%
things begin to take
a very unusual turn.

00:33:01.450 --> 00:33:03.850 align:middle line:84%
And not just Ruju,
but three sites

00:33:03.850 --> 00:33:05.410 align:middle line:90%
which are also aligned with it.

00:33:05.410 --> 00:33:08.290 align:middle line:84%
Or should I say, slightly
misaligned to each other.

00:33:08.290 --> 00:33:10.030 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at
this and I'm thinking,

00:33:10.030 --> 00:33:11.830 align:middle line:84%
these sites bear a
strong resemblance

00:33:11.830 --> 00:33:13.780 align:middle line:90%
to the belt stars of Orion.

00:33:13.780 --> 00:33:17.070 align:middle line:84%
And Orion is the
overarching constellation

00:33:17.070 --> 00:33:19.408 align:middle line:84%
in the mythology
of Sardinia, as it

00:33:19.408 --> 00:33:20.950 align:middle line:84%
is in other parts
of the world, which

00:33:20.950 --> 00:33:22.825 align:middle line:84%
brings all these people
together, by the way.

00:33:22.825 --> 00:33:25.180 align:middle line:84%
And I began to look at
the alignment of Orion,

00:33:25.180 --> 00:33:28.480 align:middle line:84%
and suddenly, 6,000 BC on
the winter solstice, bang.

00:33:28.480 --> 00:33:32.050 align:middle line:84%
You have not just the
alignment to the actual tower,

00:33:32.050 --> 00:33:35.080 align:middle line:84%
but they've artificially
flattened certain mountains

00:33:35.080 --> 00:33:37.330 align:middle line:84%
to allow for that alignment
to actually take place.

00:33:37.330 --> 00:33:38.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, we can see this.

00:33:38.240 --> 00:33:40.090 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It was a
huge dramatic theater.

00:33:40.090 --> 00:33:43.690 align:middle line:84%
But also Sirius comes up
in the same locations using

00:33:43.690 --> 00:33:46.060 align:middle line:84%
the exact same alignments,
and Sirius is always

00:33:46.060 --> 00:33:47.855 align:middle line:84%
associated with wisdom
and knowledge, which

00:33:47.855 --> 00:33:49.480 align:middle line:84%
are the people we're
talking about here

00:33:49.480 --> 00:33:50.920 align:middle line:90%
who built the towers.

00:33:50.920 --> 00:33:51.940 align:middle line:90%
So it's not just Ruju.

00:33:51.940 --> 00:33:56.090 align:middle line:84%
It's also [NON-ENGLISH]
up the road.

00:33:56.090 --> 00:33:57.366 align:middle line:90%
And also Antine.

00:33:57.366 --> 00:33:59.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Antine, which
we'll go to in just a minute.

00:33:59.850 --> 00:34:01.558 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Which we'll
go in just a minute.

00:34:01.558 --> 00:34:04.660 align:middle line:84%
And if you actually stood there
at 6,000 BC as an observer,

00:34:04.660 --> 00:34:06.810 align:middle line:84%
you would see all
these three sites

00:34:06.810 --> 00:34:10.020 align:middle line:84%
matching the winter solstice
sunrise and its sunsets.

00:34:10.020 --> 00:34:12.929 align:middle line:84%
And after the sunsets
you get Orion and Sirius

00:34:12.929 --> 00:34:15.780 align:middle line:84%
following this wonderful
dance across the sky.

00:34:15.780 --> 00:34:19.170 align:middle line:84%
And at the mid-heaven you
see it right facing Ruju.

00:34:19.170 --> 00:34:21.960 align:middle line:84%
And then at the sunset,
the setting position,

00:34:21.960 --> 00:34:23.429 align:middle line:90%
we get to Santu Antine.

00:34:23.429 --> 00:34:26.340 align:middle line:84%
And the two hills
again are perfectly

00:34:26.340 --> 00:34:29.909 align:middle line:84%
flattened to allow those
two wonderful constellations

00:34:29.909 --> 00:34:32.130 align:middle line:90%
and the star to float into.

00:34:32.130 --> 00:34:35.190 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you're talking a
huge, huge cosmic display

00:34:35.190 --> 00:34:36.870 align:middle line:84%
of archeaoastronomy,
and that gives you

00:34:36.870 --> 00:34:38.520 align:middle line:90%
a pretty good, firm date.

00:34:38.520 --> 00:34:41.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this is
approximately 3,000 years

00:34:41.010 --> 00:34:43.020 align:middle line:84%
after the great
deluge, societies

00:34:43.020 --> 00:34:44.290 align:middle line:90%
beginning to rebuild again.

00:34:44.290 --> 00:34:45.090 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:34:45.090 --> 00:34:45.389 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:34:45.389 --> 00:34:47.205 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And that's just the
stuff that's on the ground.

00:34:47.205 --> 00:34:48.455 align:middle line:90%
We don't know what's below it.

00:34:48.455 --> 00:34:51.900 align:middle line:84%
But just accepting that
as a fact, which brings

00:34:51.900 --> 00:34:54.480 align:middle line:90%
up the question of, why Orion?

00:34:54.480 --> 00:34:56.219 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And I just
still can't get over

00:34:56.219 --> 00:34:58.890 align:middle line:84%
the notion we're so
lucky that we're here

00:34:58.890 --> 00:35:01.500 align:middle line:84%
at a point in history,
we can just wander up.

00:35:01.500 --> 00:35:02.590 align:middle line:90%
There's no gatekeeper.

00:35:02.590 --> 00:35:03.718 align:middle line:90%
There's no one there.

00:35:03.718 --> 00:35:05.010 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to buy a ticket.

00:35:05.010 --> 00:35:07.607 align:middle line:84%
But all of these beautiful sites
we went to that we're looking

00:35:07.607 --> 00:35:09.690 align:middle line:84%
at right now-- and we're
going to go to number two

00:35:09.690 --> 00:35:10.560 align:middle line:90%
in a moment--

00:35:10.560 --> 00:35:14.010 align:middle line:84%
we just walked up to
unimpeded and crawled inside.

00:35:14.010 --> 00:35:16.660 align:middle line:84%
Let's hope it stays that way
for people in the future.

00:35:16.660 --> 00:35:18.150 align:middle line:10%
So now we go to Oes.

00:35:18.150 --> 00:35:19.120 align:middle line:10%
Is it called Oes?

00:35:19.120 --> 00:35:19.920 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oes.

00:35:19.920 --> 00:35:20.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oes.

00:35:20.430 --> 00:35:21.450 align:middle line:90%
We go to Oes.

00:35:21.450 --> 00:35:22.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: You're never sure
in this part of the world.

00:35:22.620 --> 00:35:23.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:35:23.100 --> 00:35:23.760 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: The language is
always a little bit dodgy.

00:35:23.760 --> 00:35:25.218 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We think
it's called Oes.

00:35:25.218 --> 00:35:29.250 align:middle line:84%
But now, this is the only
one I did not go with you to.

00:35:29.250 --> 00:35:32.750 align:middle line:84%
You went on your own, and we did
just a very brief encapsulation

00:35:32.750 --> 00:35:33.550 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:35:33.550 --> 00:35:35.760 align:middle line:84%
So tell us about
that particular site.

00:35:35.760 --> 00:35:38.190 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It was a site I
felt that had been designed

00:35:38.190 --> 00:35:40.740 align:middle line:84%
for a specific purpose and
intention originally, which

00:35:40.740 --> 00:35:41.970 align:middle line:90%
then had been expanded.

00:35:41.970 --> 00:35:45.120 align:middle line:84%
And something kind
of changed that when

00:35:45.120 --> 00:35:47.443 align:middle line:84%
it was used as a
fortification, which,

00:35:47.443 --> 00:35:49.110 align:middle line:84%
to all intents and
purposes, that's what

00:35:49.110 --> 00:35:51.300 align:middle line:90%
appears to have happened here.

00:35:51.300 --> 00:35:53.385 align:middle line:84%
There was a feel
of almost dread,

00:35:53.385 --> 00:35:57.760 align:middle line:84%
of anger, of the world
closing in on you.

00:35:57.760 --> 00:36:00.120 align:middle line:84%
So if you're able to project
your consciousness back

00:36:00.120 --> 00:36:01.537 align:middle line:84%
to the time when
it was built, you

00:36:01.537 --> 00:36:04.900 align:middle line:84%
get a sense that, OK, this was
actually a very coherent space.

00:36:04.900 --> 00:36:07.740 align:middle line:84%
It was used as a kind of
a mind projection edifice.

00:36:07.740 --> 00:36:10.345 align:middle line:84%
But then because
of time and the--

00:36:10.345 --> 00:36:11.470 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Human activities.

00:36:11.470 --> 00:36:11.770 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:36:11.770 --> 00:36:13.728 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: --and human
activity, something darker

00:36:13.728 --> 00:36:14.882 align:middle line:90%
was attached to it.

00:36:14.882 --> 00:36:17.340 align:middle line:84%
And everybody kind of felt a
little bit more sort of, well,

00:36:17.340 --> 00:36:19.890 align:middle line:84%
I think I preferred Ruju
up the road to this one,

00:36:19.890 --> 00:36:21.720 align:middle line:84%
because there hadn't
been-- it hadn't

00:36:21.720 --> 00:36:23.445 align:middle line:90%
succumbed to human folly.

00:36:23.445 --> 00:36:25.390 align:middle line:84%
It was left by itself
for some reason.

00:36:25.390 --> 00:36:26.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It was.

00:36:26.190 --> 00:36:27.280 align:middle line:90%
It was very clean.

00:36:27.280 --> 00:36:28.140 align:middle line:90%
Very clean energy.

00:36:28.140 --> 00:36:30.887 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: You sense a palpable
feel between one and the other.

00:36:30.887 --> 00:36:32.970 align:middle line:84%
And any person, normal
person would go up to these

00:36:32.970 --> 00:36:35.490 align:middle line:84%
and say, well, but they're all
towers, but no, they're not.

00:36:35.490 --> 00:36:37.180 align:middle line:90%
They're all subtly different.

00:36:37.180 --> 00:36:38.970 align:middle line:84%
That's why they have
that effect on you.

00:36:38.970 --> 00:36:39.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:36:39.300 --> 00:36:41.460 align:middle line:10%
I want to take everybody
over to Santu Antine.

00:36:41.460 --> 00:36:42.870 align:middle line:90%
Very impressive sight.

00:36:42.870 --> 00:36:45.265 align:middle line:90%
Very strange energy.

00:36:45.265 --> 00:36:48.180 align:middle line:84%
I meditated in each of the
places, as I think most of us

00:36:48.180 --> 00:36:52.800 align:middle line:84%
did, and received a really
kind of interesting look

00:36:52.800 --> 00:36:54.503 align:middle line:90%
at that one in particular.

00:36:54.503 --> 00:36:55.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Very much so.

00:36:55.420 --> 00:36:57.623 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And there was
quite a bit of fear factor,

00:36:57.623 --> 00:36:59.790 align:middle line:84%
and it was very dense, so
I was uncomfortable there.

00:36:59.790 --> 00:37:00.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

