a light box on top of the
doorway which would allow

00:39:20.300 --> 00:39:22.280 align:middle line:84%
the sunlight of
the winter solstice

00:39:22.280 --> 00:39:23.713 align:middle line:84%
to come flooding
into the chamber.

00:39:23.713 --> 00:39:25.880 align:middle line:84%
Why would you block that
with a wall in front of it?

00:39:25.880 --> 00:39:27.470 align:middle line:84%
And that's what you
were picking up as well

00:39:27.470 --> 00:39:29.180 align:middle line:84%
was the later stage
where they turned it

00:39:29.180 --> 00:39:30.740 align:middle line:90%
into a big fortification.

00:39:30.740 --> 00:39:33.740 align:middle line:84%
And now it's like a labyrinth
of corridors and towers.

00:39:33.740 --> 00:39:37.070 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, and you can see the
progression from knowledge

00:39:37.070 --> 00:39:40.070 align:middle line:84%
to spirituality to
fear, which brings us

00:39:40.070 --> 00:39:44.030 align:middle line:84%
into the historic period
of about 1500, 2000 BC.

00:39:44.030 --> 00:39:45.800 align:middle line:84%
There were marauding
people on Sardinia

00:39:45.800 --> 00:39:48.930 align:middle line:84%
and now we can establish
that as a fact.

00:39:48.930 --> 00:39:51.382 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: All these little
crevices and walkways.

00:39:51.382 --> 00:39:53.090 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: These were
built for big people.

00:39:53.090 --> 00:39:53.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:39:53.890 --> 00:39:58.810 align:middle line:90%


00:39:58.810 --> 00:40:01.420 align:middle line:84%
So Freddy, you've
never seen this

00:40:01.420 --> 00:40:05.080 align:middle line:84%
before where the beehive we were
just in, that little chamber we

00:40:05.080 --> 00:40:08.650 align:middle line:84%
meditated in for a bit,
we're now standing above it,

00:40:08.650 --> 00:40:09.928 align:middle line:90%
and there's a second beehive.

00:40:09.928 --> 00:40:11.470 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Short
beehive chamber, which

00:40:11.470 --> 00:40:14.020 align:middle line:84%
seems to be about half the
size of the one below it.

00:40:14.020 --> 00:40:16.390 align:middle line:84%
And it faces out onto
a beautiful window,

00:40:16.390 --> 00:40:18.410 align:middle line:84%
again, with a
light box above it,

00:40:18.410 --> 00:40:21.310 align:middle line:84%
which is usually a sign that
it's pointing to a rising

00:40:21.310 --> 00:40:25.450 align:middle line:84%
object so that the light comes
in here, hits the alcove,

00:40:25.450 --> 00:40:29.627 align:middle line:84%
and that seems to, again,
match the sunrise in 6000 BC.

00:40:29.627 --> 00:40:31.210 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But look
at the construction

00:40:31.210 --> 00:40:32.825 align:middle line:90%
compared to the one below.

00:40:32.825 --> 00:40:34.200 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: But here's
the fun part,

00:40:34.200 --> 00:40:36.708 align:middle line:84%
and this is where we have to
do a bit of lateral thinking.

00:40:36.708 --> 00:40:38.500 align:middle line:84%
So whatever it was, it
was important enough

00:40:38.500 --> 00:40:41.350 align:middle line:84%
to measure some object
rising on the horizon

00:40:41.350 --> 00:40:43.840 align:middle line:84%
twice, because you'd
see it here first

00:40:43.840 --> 00:40:46.540 align:middle line:84%
and then you'd go down
to the floor below

00:40:46.540 --> 00:40:49.010 align:middle line:90%
and you see it rising up again.

00:40:49.010 --> 00:40:50.510 align:middle line:84%
So it's obviously
important enough--

00:40:50.510 --> 00:40:53.135 align:middle line:84%
it could have been the fact that
there's two objects rising one

00:40:53.135 --> 00:40:54.100 align:middle line:90%
above the other.

00:40:54.100 --> 00:40:56.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and it's
also thought in the Sardinian

00:40:56.350 --> 00:41:00.160 align:middle line:84%
history, again, one of the
researchers here that's been

00:41:00.160 --> 00:41:03.340 align:middle line:84%
on it for a lot of years,
Sergio Frau believes--

00:41:03.340 --> 00:41:07.240 align:middle line:84%
and this aligns with some of the
great philosophers of Greece--

00:41:07.240 --> 00:41:09.460 align:middle line:84%
that there was another
deluge that happened where

00:41:09.460 --> 00:41:10.840 align:middle line:90%
the coastline was inundated.

00:41:10.840 --> 00:41:13.870 align:middle line:84%
And they say the evidence
they found was almost like--

00:41:13.870 --> 00:41:15.560 align:middle line:90%
they called it a mud Pompeii.

00:41:15.560 --> 00:41:16.360 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: [LAUGHS]

00:41:16.360 --> 00:41:19.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You know, jewelry,
pots, pieces of pottery

00:41:19.480 --> 00:41:23.260 align:middle line:84%
and dishes all roiled
together in this mud.

00:41:23.260 --> 00:41:24.850 align:middle line:84%
So it may have been--
and they believe

00:41:24.850 --> 00:41:28.120 align:middle line:84%
that there was a piece
of meteorite that

00:41:28.120 --> 00:41:30.890 align:middle line:84%
crashed into the
environment in the sea,

00:41:30.890 --> 00:41:33.510 align:middle line:84%
and it crashes in-- apparently,
I think they calculate it

00:41:33.510 --> 00:41:37.060 align:middle line:84%
at 20 kilometers a second, which
creates quite a tidal wave,

00:41:37.060 --> 00:41:39.520 align:middle line:84%
so the coastal regions
were wiped out again.

00:41:39.520 --> 00:41:41.242 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yes, exactly.

00:41:41.242 --> 00:41:43.450 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's around 3000
BC, if I'm not mistaken.

00:41:43.450 --> 00:41:46.300 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I think
they say around 3100, 3200.

00:41:46.300 --> 00:41:50.330 align:middle line:84%
I think one of the
guesses was 1175 BC.

00:41:50.330 --> 00:41:51.130 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:41:51.130 --> 00:41:52.150 align:middle line:90%
It shifted the weather.

00:41:52.150 --> 00:41:54.883 align:middle line:90%
It shifted apparently the stars.

00:41:54.883 --> 00:41:57.550 align:middle line:84%
The actual rotation of the Earth
actually stopped for a few days

00:41:57.550 --> 00:42:00.490 align:middle line:84%
because they talk about in
Asia, actually in China,

00:42:00.490 --> 00:42:02.170 align:middle line:84%
the sun staying in
the sky for three

00:42:02.170 --> 00:42:03.400 align:middle line:90%
days in the same location.

00:42:03.400 --> 00:42:04.990 align:middle line:84%
And on the opposite
side of the world,

00:42:04.990 --> 00:42:07.480 align:middle line:84%
the moon stayed in the same
location for three days.

00:42:07.480 --> 00:42:08.530 align:middle line:90%
Everything stopped.

00:42:08.530 --> 00:42:12.070 align:middle line:84%
And from that moment, we go from
a spiritual concept of the land

00:42:12.070 --> 00:42:14.920 align:middle line:84%
to a much more
protective concept.

00:42:14.920 --> 00:42:16.295 align:middle line:84%
People are now
working with fear.

00:42:16.295 --> 00:42:17.795 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're
working with fear.

00:42:17.795 --> 00:42:20.350 align:middle line:84%
They're hiding anywhere they
can just to sustain themselves.

00:42:20.350 --> 00:42:21.767 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And that's
when you begin

00:42:21.767 --> 00:42:23.770 align:middle line:84%
to adapt the old sites
to a protective state.

00:42:23.770 --> 00:42:26.120 align:middle line:84%
And we see that in Northern
Europe as well in England,

00:42:26.120 --> 00:42:26.920 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:42:26.920 --> 00:42:31.000 align:middle line:84%
Stonehenge goes from being one
circle to being two circles.

00:42:31.000 --> 00:42:33.190 align:middle line:84%
They began to re-adapt
the sacred sites

00:42:33.190 --> 00:42:34.730 align:middle line:84%
to the new alignments
in the sky.

00:42:34.730 --> 00:42:36.490 align:middle line:84%
So that's been played
out here as well.

00:42:36.490 --> 00:42:38.890 align:middle line:84%
And yes, there was a comet
that hit the Mediterranean,

00:42:38.890 --> 00:42:40.590 align:middle line:84%
and it did create
a lot of havoc.

00:42:40.590 --> 00:42:42.340 align:middle line:84%
And it wiped out-- it
was also responsible

00:42:42.340 --> 00:42:45.550 align:middle line:84%
for wiping out part of the
Bronze Age culture later.

00:42:45.550 --> 00:42:49.150 align:middle line:84%
There's another event that
happened later on after that.

00:42:49.150 --> 00:42:51.020 align:middle line:84%
We live in a very
volatile solar system.

00:42:51.020 --> 00:42:52.600 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the
ancients kept saying

00:42:52.600 --> 00:42:54.610 align:middle line:84%
that in no way are
the-- actually,

00:42:54.610 --> 00:42:57.520 align:middle line:84%
this is a direct quote
from the Chinese.

00:42:57.520 --> 00:43:00.160 align:middle line:84%
In no way are the orbits
of the planets fixed.

00:43:00.160 --> 00:43:02.890 align:middle line:84%
Once in a while, things come
from outside the solar system

00:43:02.890 --> 00:43:05.350 align:middle line:84%
and it hits the planets,
shakes them off their orbits,

00:43:05.350 --> 00:43:08.120 align:middle line:84%
and then it influences us,
and things hit us as well.

00:43:08.120 --> 00:43:12.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we've had 13 cataclysms
since the flood in 9700 BC.

00:43:12.610 --> 00:43:15.200 align:middle line:84%
So we live in fairly
interesting times all the time.

00:43:15.200 --> 00:43:16.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We do.

00:43:16.000 --> 00:43:18.500 align:middle line:84%
And I think sometimes
when people hear this,

00:43:18.500 --> 00:43:22.180 align:middle line:84%
it gives a sense of
futility to being human.

00:43:22.180 --> 00:43:23.560 align:middle line:90%
It's like, this isn't fair.

00:43:23.560 --> 00:43:24.700 align:middle line:90%
We build it up.

00:43:24.700 --> 00:43:26.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's like
watching someone smash

00:43:26.440 --> 00:43:29.750 align:middle line:84%
some little kid's sandcastle
and you start all over again,

00:43:29.750 --> 00:43:30.940 align:middle line:90%
except with no memory--

00:43:30.940 --> 00:43:33.280 align:middle line:84%
we'll talk about that in a
little bit-- with no memory,

00:43:33.280 --> 00:43:35.360 align:middle line:84%
starting again and
again and again.

00:43:35.360 --> 00:43:37.300 align:middle line:90%
So this happened once again.

00:43:37.300 --> 00:43:40.313 align:middle line:84%
But there are these
markers of consistency.

00:43:40.313 --> 00:43:41.980 align:middle line:84%
So the whole point
of this is that there

00:43:41.980 --> 00:43:44.692 align:middle line:84%
was an advanced civilization
that originally settled it,

00:43:44.692 --> 00:43:46.150 align:middle line:84%
and many of these
nuraghe have been

00:43:46.150 --> 00:43:49.760 align:middle line:84%
built upon by subsequent
invaders, colonizers,

00:43:49.760 --> 00:43:50.560 align:middle line:90%
and so forth?

00:43:50.560 --> 00:43:51.130 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

00:43:51.130 --> 00:43:51.820 align:middle line:90%
It's been adapted.

00:43:51.820 --> 00:43:53.278 align:middle line:84%
You can look at
all the stuff here.

00:43:53.278 --> 00:43:56.440 align:middle line:84%
This was all adaptation for
habitation much, much later.

00:43:56.440 --> 00:43:59.100 align:middle line:84%
Again, when you have a site
that's 8,000 years old,

00:43:59.100 --> 00:44:00.850 align:middle line:84%
it's going to go through
a lot of changes,

00:44:00.850 --> 00:44:01.840 align:middle line:90%
a lot of adaptations.

00:44:01.840 --> 00:44:03.882 align:middle line:84%
And you can see it where
things have been adapted

00:44:03.882 --> 00:44:05.380 align:middle line:90%
that don't quite make sense.

00:44:05.380 --> 00:44:07.000 align:middle line:90%
It's more utilitarian.

00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:10.780 align:middle line:84%
The rest of it's simply much
more astronomically aligned.

00:44:10.780 --> 00:44:13.900 align:middle line:84%
It's much more purposeful in
terms of a spiritual context.

00:44:13.900 --> 00:44:16.750 align:middle line:84%
And that wouldn't serve
people who were being raided.

00:44:16.750 --> 00:44:19.270 align:middle line:84%
We're now talking
about 1,500 BC where

00:44:19.270 --> 00:44:20.890 align:middle line:84%
there was a lot of
raiding going on

00:44:20.890 --> 00:44:23.050 align:middle line:84%
in Sardinia, so
it follows nicely

00:44:23.050 --> 00:44:24.220 align:middle line:90%
with the historical track.

00:44:24.220 --> 00:44:25.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:44:25.020 --> 00:44:26.500 align:middle line:90%
Indeed.

00:44:26.500 --> 00:44:30.700 align:middle line:84%
So as random and
inconsistent, the effect

00:44:30.700 --> 00:44:33.070 align:middle line:84%
it has on this species,
this amnesiac sense

00:44:33.070 --> 00:44:35.890 align:middle line:84%
of having to drag ourselves
up and start over, again,

00:44:35.890 --> 00:44:39.850 align:middle line:84%
all over the world, there are
some markers of consistency.

00:44:39.850 --> 00:44:43.270 align:middle line:84%
And it always seems to point
back, as we mentioned earlier,

00:44:43.270 --> 00:44:46.010 align:middle line:84%
in these-- at least these
sacred sites around the world

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:46.810 align:middle line:90%
to Orion.

00:44:46.810 --> 00:44:47.650 align:middle line:90%
Why Orion?

00:44:47.650 --> 00:44:51.813 align:middle line:84%
What's the significance of
Orion to this planet and to us?

00:44:51.813 --> 00:44:53.230 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: That was
the big question

00:44:53.230 --> 00:44:55.210 align:middle line:84%
I was asking for
the book project,

00:44:55.210 --> 00:44:58.030 align:middle line:84%
and that was, why do all the
cultures around the Earth

00:44:58.030 --> 00:44:58.870 align:middle line:90%
talk about Orion?

00:44:58.870 --> 00:45:00.160 align:middle line:90%
What is the significance?

00:45:00.160 --> 00:45:02.810 align:middle line:84%
I mean, yeah, we look out of
the sky on a balcony and we go,

00:45:02.810 --> 00:45:03.610 align:middle line:90%
there's Orion.

00:45:03.610 --> 00:45:06.370 align:middle line:84%
It's a pretty--
it's in your face.

00:45:06.370 --> 00:45:08.560 align:middle line:84%
But more importantly,
why are they

00:45:08.560 --> 00:45:11.650 align:middle line:84%
so adamant about it being
the half of the universe,

00:45:11.650 --> 00:45:14.050 align:middle line:84%
the light of heaven,
the light of the sky,

00:45:14.050 --> 00:45:14.955 align:middle line:90%
a point of creation?

00:45:14.955 --> 00:45:16.330 align:middle line:84%
It depends who
you're talking to.

00:45:16.330 --> 00:45:17.622 align:middle line:90%
They talk about the same thing.

00:45:17.622 --> 00:45:21.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turns out that one of
the original sages of the Anu

00:45:21.430 --> 00:45:22.960 align:middle line:90%
was called Uanna.

00:45:22.960 --> 00:45:24.550 align:middle line:90%
That's where Orion comes from.

00:45:24.550 --> 00:45:28.090 align:middle line:84%
Orion is a Greek
translation of Sumerian.

00:45:28.090 --> 00:45:32.770 align:middle line:84%
So Uanna was actually one of
the main priests, the magician

00:45:32.770 --> 00:45:35.260 align:middle line:90%
priests of the people of Anu.

00:45:35.260 --> 00:45:37.950 align:middle line:84%
Which brings us back again to
Sardinia and the tall people.

00:45:37.950 --> 00:45:38.950 align:middle line:90%
And they were very tall.

00:45:38.950 --> 00:45:40.420 align:middle line:90%
There were seven sages.

00:45:40.420 --> 00:45:43.780 align:middle line:84%
And that these were the people
that basically come from this--

00:45:43.780 --> 00:45:45.610 align:middle line:84%
they either come
from Orion, or they

00:45:45.610 --> 00:45:47.590 align:middle line:84%
have a spiritual
connection to Orion,

00:45:47.590 --> 00:45:49.900 align:middle line:84%
or they found the way
to go from the physical

00:45:49.900 --> 00:45:52.000 align:middle line:90%
to the spiritual in Orion.

00:45:52.000 --> 00:45:54.712 align:middle line:84%
Again, it's the same story
overlapping around the world.

00:45:54.712 --> 00:45:56.420 align:middle line:84%
And the more I talk
to Indigenous people,

00:45:56.420 --> 00:45:58.270 align:middle line:84%
the more they say
actually, it's all three.

00:45:58.270 --> 00:46:01.330 align:middle line:84%
It's a metaphor, a symbol,
and back in the day

00:46:01.330 --> 00:46:03.100 align:middle line:84%
they could go
backwards and forwards

00:46:03.100 --> 00:46:05.350 align:middle line:84%
in this sort of portal,
this tube they called it

00:46:05.350 --> 00:46:06.520 align:middle line:90%
between the stars.

00:46:06.520 --> 00:46:09.110 align:middle line:84%
And they go there
because they could.

00:46:09.110 --> 00:46:11.560 align:middle line:84%
They had this understanding
of the laws of nature,

00:46:11.560 --> 00:46:13.190 align:middle line:90%
which sounds strange to us.

00:46:13.190 --> 00:46:15.970 align:middle line:84%
But when you hear this again
and again around the world

00:46:15.970 --> 00:46:18.580 align:middle line:84%
and you see that these people
were human-like and yet

00:46:18.580 --> 00:46:20.620 align:middle line:84%
not quite human,
you begin to wonder,

00:46:20.620 --> 00:46:24.280 align:middle line:84%
was this perhaps something to
do with a group of people that

00:46:24.280 --> 00:46:26.530 align:middle line:84%
were either stationed
here, were dropped here,

00:46:26.530 --> 00:46:28.970 align:middle line:84%
or were left here from
a long, long time ago?

00:46:28.970 --> 00:46:31.552 align:middle line:84%
Which in my mind
suggests this is

00:46:31.552 --> 00:46:33.010 align:middle line:84%
why they didn't
want to communicate

00:46:33.010 --> 00:46:34.570 align:middle line:90%
with humans that much.

00:46:34.570 --> 00:46:38.268 align:middle line:84%
They wanted to be a society
aside from human people.

00:46:38.268 --> 00:46:40.060 align:middle line:84%
They had a complete
different understanding

00:46:40.060 --> 00:46:41.410 align:middle line:90%
to hunter gatherers.

00:46:41.410 --> 00:46:44.230 align:middle line:84%
And in order to live here in
harmony with human beings,

00:46:44.230 --> 00:46:46.510 align:middle line:84%
they had to divulge the
information that they

00:46:46.510 --> 00:46:48.910 align:middle line:90%
had, slowly drip feeding it.

00:46:48.910 --> 00:46:51.220 align:middle line:84%
And we see the vestiges
of their culture

00:46:51.220 --> 00:46:56.110 align:middle line:84%
in the words, the deeds, the
mythology, and also the things

00:46:56.110 --> 00:46:57.820 align:middle line:84%
that they built,
because wherever

00:46:57.820 --> 00:47:00.460 align:middle line:84%
you go from whether it's
the Mediterranean all

00:47:00.460 --> 00:47:02.590 align:middle line:84%
the way to Central
America or South America,

00:47:02.590 --> 00:47:04.120 align:middle line:84%
the same construction
technology.

00:47:04.120 --> 00:47:07.010 align:middle line:84%
And it's the same people that
are doing it all the time.

00:47:07.010 --> 00:47:08.600 align:middle line:84%
So that's why Orion
was important.

00:47:08.600 --> 00:47:11.950 align:middle line:84%
It seems to be a creative point
in the center of the universe

00:47:11.950 --> 00:47:13.960 align:middle line:84%
that all Indigenous
people go back to again

00:47:13.960 --> 00:47:15.293 align:middle line:90%
and again and again.

00:47:15.293 --> 00:47:16.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:47:16.210 --> 00:47:18.670 align:middle line:84%
And now I'll tell you another
a little bit of esoterica.

00:47:18.670 --> 00:47:21.940 align:middle line:84%
Two unrelated sources
were sharing with me

00:47:21.940 --> 00:47:24.880 align:middle line:84%
the journey of the watchers
in different times,

00:47:24.880 --> 00:47:26.240 align:middle line:90%
different interviews, and such.

00:47:26.240 --> 00:47:29.350 align:middle line:84%
And one of them was
saying that the people--

00:47:29.350 --> 00:47:31.420 align:middle line:84%
these beings, these
nonphysical beings

00:47:31.420 --> 00:47:33.490 align:middle line:84%
went through a process
of densification

00:47:33.490 --> 00:47:35.810 align:middle line:84%
in order to be of service
wherever they were.

00:47:35.810 --> 00:47:37.750 align:middle line:84%
And one of them--
before coming to Earth,

00:47:37.750 --> 00:47:40.450 align:middle line:84%
one of the trajectories
was considered

00:47:40.450 --> 00:47:44.290 align:middle line:84%
to be from the Crab
Nebula through to Orion,

00:47:44.290 --> 00:47:46.120 align:middle line:90%
to Sirius, Venus, Earth.

00:47:46.120 --> 00:47:49.420 align:middle line:84%
And this was the trajectory,
becoming more and more and more

00:47:49.420 --> 00:47:53.107 align:middle line:84%
third dimensional in the process
to be able to be in this given

00:47:53.107 --> 00:47:54.940 align:middle line:84%
place-- and I'm sure
there are many others--

00:47:54.940 --> 00:47:58.090 align:middle line:84%
to be able to hold energies,
hold knowledge, and be

00:47:58.090 --> 00:48:00.470 align:middle line:90%
of service when help was needed.

00:48:00.470 --> 00:48:02.200 align:middle line:84%
Which is the journey
of the watchers.

00:48:02.200 --> 00:48:03.160 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And that's
something that

00:48:03.160 --> 00:48:05.320 align:middle line:84%
pops up again in traditions
all around the world.

00:48:05.320 --> 00:48:08.250 align:middle line:84%
The watchers could take on human
form "whenever they wanted,"

00:48:08.250 --> 00:48:09.130 align:middle line:90%
quote.

00:48:09.130 --> 00:48:10.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: But not easily.

00:48:10.270 --> 00:48:10.780 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Not easily.

00:48:10.780 --> 00:48:12.197 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have
a good time here.

00:48:12.197 --> 00:48:14.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Very, very
difficult for their being.

00:48:14.200 --> 00:48:14.470 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:48:14.470 --> 00:48:16.345 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: They had to
have the tall structure.

00:48:16.345 --> 00:48:18.130 align:middle line:10%
They had the elongated
skulls, which

00:48:18.130 --> 00:48:21.610 align:middle line:10%
we find in Sardinia and in other
pinch points around the world.

00:48:21.610 --> 00:48:23.380 align:middle line:10%
They had the red hair.

00:48:23.380 --> 00:48:25.240 align:middle line:10%
But they said, we
had a hard time

00:48:25.240 --> 00:48:28.130 align:middle line:10%
being here because it was such
a physical, dense dimension.

00:48:28.130 --> 00:48:28.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:48:28.930 --> 00:48:30.700 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So for
anyone who understands

00:48:30.700 --> 00:48:33.580 align:middle line:84%
molecular structures and the
mechanics of nature, for them

00:48:33.580 --> 00:48:38.080 align:middle line:84%
it was easy as you and I going
shopping to buy a bowl of soup.

00:48:38.080 --> 00:48:39.783 align:middle line:84%
They could just bend
nature like that

00:48:39.783 --> 00:48:41.450 align:middle line:84%
and they could be in
two places at once.

00:48:41.450 --> 00:48:43.840 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly it makes
sense, because again,

00:48:43.840 --> 00:48:46.900 align:middle line:84%
if these people 10,000,
11,000 years ago,

00:48:46.900 --> 00:48:49.000 align:middle line:84%
if they weren't
communicating with each other

00:48:49.000 --> 00:48:51.550 align:middle line:84%
according to
Orthodox belief, how

00:48:51.550 --> 00:48:54.010 align:middle line:84%
is it that the stories
overlap, and in some cases are

00:48:54.010 --> 00:48:55.070 align:middle line:90%
practically identical?

00:48:55.070 --> 00:48:55.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:48:55.870 --> 00:48:57.400 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: They had to come
from a central source,

00:48:57.400 --> 00:48:59.440 align:middle line:84%
and everybody was
sharing the same story,

00:48:59.440 --> 00:49:01.900 align:middle line:84%
and they were all in contact
with the same people.

00:49:01.900 --> 00:49:04.090 align:middle line:84%
And that's what fascinates
me, the fact that we do

00:49:04.090 --> 00:49:07.510 align:middle line:84%
have a parallel civilization
working with humans,

00:49:07.510 --> 00:49:10.070 align:middle line:84%
and this is why humans were
not really afraid of them.

00:49:10.070 --> 00:49:12.160 align:middle line:84%
They felt them to
be very helpful.

00:49:12.160 --> 00:49:14.980 align:middle line:84%
And after the deluge,
there were groups

00:49:14.980 --> 00:49:17.260 align:middle line:84%
which came-- appeared
suddenly all around the world

00:49:17.260 --> 00:49:19.150 align:middle line:90%
at strategic points.

00:49:19.150 --> 00:49:20.650 align:middle line:90%
Seven people, seven sages.

00:49:20.650 --> 00:49:21.550 align:middle line:90%
One was a woman.

00:49:21.550 --> 00:49:24.670 align:middle line:84%
And there was an eighth central
figure with the large eyes,

00:49:24.670 --> 00:49:27.430 align:middle line:84%
and he was married to
this woman of wisdom

00:49:27.430 --> 00:49:29.800 align:middle line:84%
who was also his sister,
which I believe to be a symbol

00:49:29.800 --> 00:49:30.130 align:middle line:90%
more than--

00:49:30.130 --> 00:49:31.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or Isis and Osiris.

00:49:31.670 --> 00:49:33.160 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah, Isis and Osiris.

00:49:33.160 --> 00:49:34.900 align:middle line:90%
Viracocha and his wife.

00:49:34.900 --> 00:49:37.180 align:middle line:84%
Even the Waitaha
of New Zealand who

00:49:37.180 --> 00:49:39.880 align:middle line:84%
have an oral tradition
spanning 12,000 years,

00:49:39.880 --> 00:49:41.860 align:middle line:84%
they talk about the
same people as well.

00:49:41.860 --> 00:49:43.997 align:middle line:84%
And it was their
charge to then rebuild

00:49:43.997 --> 00:49:45.580 align:middle line:84%
in the names of the
Egyptians-- and it

00:49:45.580 --> 00:49:48.680 align:middle line:84%
was the Egyptians-- rebuild
the former world of the gods.

00:49:48.680 --> 00:49:49.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:49:49.480 --> 00:49:51.910 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Rebuild the
temples in the image

00:49:51.910 --> 00:49:53.320 align:middle line:90%
from where they had come from.

00:49:53.320 --> 00:49:55.600 align:middle line:84%
And this explains why
the temples appear out

00:49:55.600 --> 00:49:57.780 align:middle line:84%
of nowhere, completely
constructed,

00:49:57.780 --> 00:50:00.090 align:middle line:84%
complete mythologies,
complete understanding

00:50:00.090 --> 00:50:02.380 align:middle line:84%
of the laws of physics,
mathematics, astrology,

00:50:02.380 --> 00:50:03.638 align:middle line:90%
and astronomy.

00:50:03.638 --> 00:50:04.680 align:middle line:90%
Where did this come from?

00:50:04.680 --> 00:50:07.080 align:middle line:84%
Unless they were hallucinating,
which I am open to.

00:50:07.080 --> 00:50:07.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Collectively.

00:50:07.550 --> 00:50:08.490 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Collectively.

00:50:08.490 --> 00:50:10.650 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
every sixth civilization

00:50:10.650 --> 00:50:14.110 align:middle line:84%
arrives prepackaged like
IKEA just drops by and says,

00:50:14.110 --> 00:50:15.143 align:middle line:90%
OK, here's a temple.

00:50:15.143 --> 00:50:16.560 align:middle line:84%
We've really come
up with a story.

00:50:16.560 --> 00:50:17.190 align:middle line:90%
Just build it.

00:50:17.190 --> 00:50:18.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Here are
your furnishings.

00:50:18.120 --> 00:50:18.630 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:50:18.630 --> 00:50:19.713 align:middle line:90%
Here are your furnishings.

00:50:19.713 --> 00:50:22.350 align:middle line:84%
And that explained-- suddenly
everything falls into place

00:50:22.350 --> 00:50:25.050 align:middle line:84%
when you recognize that
there was a parallel culture.

00:50:25.050 --> 00:50:26.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk
about something else.

00:50:26.800 --> 00:50:28.550 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
throw this in before we

00:50:28.550 --> 00:50:31.470 align:middle line:84%
go to another one of the sites,
the most famous site here,

00:50:31.470 --> 00:50:34.860 align:middle line:84%
Barumini But before
that, now we've

00:50:34.860 --> 00:50:38.400 align:middle line:84%
just laid down the history
of why Orion is significant.

00:50:38.400 --> 00:50:41.550 align:middle line:84%
But the giants and the
presence of these people,

00:50:41.550 --> 00:50:44.140 align:middle line:84%
let's go to the Solomon
Islands because I found--

00:50:44.140 --> 00:50:44.940 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know this.

00:50:44.940 --> 00:50:47.760 align:middle line:84%
You told this to us when we were
driving in the car, in the van

00:50:47.760 --> 00:50:48.180 align:middle line:90%
yesterday.

00:50:48.180 --> 00:50:49.110 align:middle line:90%
This is fascinating.

00:50:49.110 --> 00:50:51.120 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yes, I had no
intention of talking

00:50:51.120 --> 00:50:52.557 align:middle line:90%
about giants in the book.

00:50:52.557 --> 00:50:54.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You talked
about it several times.

00:50:54.390 --> 00:50:56.460 align:middle line:84%
And again, that's
why I kept saying,

00:50:56.460 --> 00:50:58.270 align:middle line:84%
Freddy, we need
to do this thing.

00:50:58.270 --> 00:50:59.070 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:50:59.070 --> 00:51:01.260 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Because it was
a whole story in itself.

00:51:01.260 --> 00:51:03.480 align:middle line:84%
There's tall people and
then there's giant people.

00:51:03.480 --> 00:51:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And the more I kept
reading about the stories--

00:51:05.700 --> 00:51:07.180 align:middle line:84%
again, starting
with New Zealand,

00:51:07.180 --> 00:51:09.763 align:middle line:84%
which, hardly anyone knows about
the prehistory of New Zealand

00:51:09.763 --> 00:51:12.030 align:middle line:84%
apart from this group of
people called the Waitaha.

00:51:12.030 --> 00:51:15.150 align:middle line:84%
And they said every year when we
used to live in Easter Island,

00:51:15.150 --> 00:51:18.663 align:middle line:84%
11,000 years ago before the
flood, the gods used to come

00:51:18.663 --> 00:51:19.830 align:middle line:90%
around and hang out with us.

00:51:19.830 --> 00:51:23.070 align:middle line:84%
And they were very tall, very
puissant, beautiful people.

00:51:23.070 --> 00:51:24.023 align:middle line:90%
Light skins.

00:51:24.023 --> 00:51:25.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
that's thought to be

00:51:25.440 --> 00:51:29.350 align:middle line:84%
the remaining-- the remnant
of Lemuria, Easter Island is.

00:51:29.350 --> 00:51:30.910 align:middle line:84%
So let's go ahead--
so again, we just

00:51:30.910 --> 00:51:32.910 align:middle line:84%
start looking at some of
the migration patterns.

00:51:32.910 --> 00:51:33.420 align:middle line:90%
Go ahead.

00:51:33.420 --> 00:51:33.720 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:51:33.720 --> 00:51:34.440 align:middle line:90%
And they were everywhere.

00:51:34.440 --> 00:51:36.660 align:middle line:84%
And they got around easily
as you and I go shopping

00:51:36.660 --> 00:51:38.700 align:middle line:84%
at the supermarket
because they used

00:51:38.700 --> 00:51:40.800 align:middle line:84%
mostly catamarans from
what I understand.

00:51:40.800 --> 00:51:41.970 align:middle line:90%
Massive ships.

00:51:41.970 --> 00:51:44.700 align:middle line:84%
People in Tonga still
build them the same way.

00:51:44.700 --> 00:51:48.090 align:middle line:84%
And they basically set up
bases in strategic part

00:51:48.090 --> 00:51:51.510 align:middle line:84%
of the world, which became known
as the birthplaces of the gods

00:51:51.510 --> 00:51:54.150 align:middle line:84%
or the navel of the
Earth, and so forth.

00:51:54.150 --> 00:51:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And whenever you
go to these places,

00:51:55.750 --> 00:52:00.160 align:middle line:84%
you do see a sudden flowering of
civilization, megalithic temple

00:52:00.160 --> 00:52:00.960 align:middle line:90%
building.

00:52:00.960 --> 00:52:04.080 align:middle line:84%
And the knowledge which
forms the foundation

00:52:04.080 --> 00:52:06.720 align:middle line:84%
of all civilization
spreads out like ripples

00:52:06.720 --> 00:52:09.690 align:middle line:84%
in a pond to all the people
that come within their vicinity.

00:52:09.690 --> 00:52:11.400 align:middle line:84%
And this is where
humans start developing

00:52:11.400 --> 00:52:14.640 align:middle line:84%
that sense of community
and agriculture

00:52:14.640 --> 00:52:17.460 align:middle line:84%
and starts developing
there then in turn.

00:52:17.460 --> 00:52:19.830 align:middle line:84%
And this is why the gods
were so appreciated.

00:52:19.830 --> 00:52:21.810 align:middle line:84%
They took them out
of a big problem

00:52:21.810 --> 00:52:24.000 align:middle line:84%
where everybody's living
in barbaric states

00:52:24.000 --> 00:52:27.450 align:middle line:84%
after everything's completely
run over by massive waves,

00:52:27.450 --> 00:52:30.018 align:middle line:84%
and they gave them the
accouterments of civilization.

00:52:30.018 --> 00:52:31.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But in
the Solomon Islands,

00:52:31.560 --> 00:52:33.377 align:middle line:90%
we're not speaking past tense.

00:52:33.377 --> 00:52:35.460 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: We're still talking
in the present tense.

00:52:35.460 --> 00:52:37.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk
about these beings

00:52:37.470 --> 00:52:40.340 align:middle line:84%
and some of your
odd experiences.

00:52:40.340 --> 00:52:41.440 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: [LAUGHS]

00:52:41.440 --> 00:52:42.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: This is fascinating.

00:52:42.690 --> 00:52:43.530 align:middle line:90%
Can you talk about it?

00:52:43.530 --> 00:52:44.330 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:52:44.330 --> 00:52:46.410 align:middle line:84%
Going back to the
Solomon Islands,

00:52:46.410 --> 00:52:51.120 align:middle line:84%
I found that in the Polynesia
area there's a lot of stories

00:52:51.120 --> 00:52:55.080 align:middle line:84%
going back into the '50s and
the 1920s of ordinary people,

00:52:55.080 --> 00:52:56.760 align:middle line:90%
a young child going--

00:52:56.760 --> 00:52:59.940 align:middle line:84%
walking in the beach and coming
across a massive skeleton.

00:52:59.940 --> 00:53:01.590 align:middle line:90%
The flesh is still attached.

00:53:01.590 --> 00:53:02.730 align:middle line:90%
And it's not a whale.

00:53:02.730 --> 00:53:03.570 align:middle line:90%
It's not a dolphin.

00:53:03.570 --> 00:53:05.050 align:middle line:90%
It's a human being.

00:53:05.050 --> 00:53:06.730 align:middle line:90%
And a couple of them stand out.

00:53:06.730 --> 00:53:08.580 align:middle line:90%
One of them was 18 feet tall.

00:53:08.580 --> 00:53:11.358 align:middle line:84%
And there was a record of it
where a flatbed truck comes

00:53:11.358 --> 00:53:12.900 align:middle line:84%
over from the local
counsel, picks up

00:53:12.900 --> 00:53:16.170 align:middle line:84%
this massive person,
red hair still attached.

00:53:16.170 --> 00:53:18.038 align:middle line:84%
They put him on the
back of the truck,

00:53:18.038 --> 00:53:19.830 align:middle line:84%
and that's the last
time you hear about it.

00:53:19.830 --> 00:53:21.150 align:middle line:90%
Official secrets act, boom.

00:53:21.150 --> 00:53:21.450 align:middle line:90%
Stamped.

00:53:21.450 --> 00:53:22.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:53:22.250 --> 00:53:24.270 align:middle line:84%
They always disappear,
all over the world.

00:53:24.270 --> 00:53:27.540 align:middle line:84%
America's one of the
worst at spiriting away

00:53:27.540 --> 00:53:30.390 align:middle line:84%
the giants that are in all of
these Native American lands

00:53:30.390 --> 00:53:33.400 align:middle line:84%
around the country, including
California, Nevada, Arizona,

00:53:33.400 --> 00:53:36.270 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, and of course,
the Midwest, the famous ones

00:53:36.270 --> 00:53:37.710 align:middle line:90%
in Ohio, Michigan.

00:53:37.710 --> 00:53:39.335 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: No different
to anywhere else.

00:53:39.335 --> 00:53:41.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Every country
takes these bones.

00:53:41.130 --> 00:53:43.320 align:middle line:84%
Some official organization
or institution

00:53:43.320 --> 00:53:44.340 align:middle line:90%
comes and gets them.

00:53:44.340 --> 00:53:45.990 align:middle line:90%
You never hear about it again.

00:53:45.990 --> 00:53:49.088 align:middle line:84%
But they're still present,
so this is interesting.

00:53:49.088 --> 00:53:50.130 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Solomon Islands.

00:53:50.130 --> 00:53:53.850 align:middle line:84%
And in the Second World War
when the US Navy personnel was

00:53:53.850 --> 00:53:56.520 align:middle line:84%
stationed there, they said,
we all slept with a revolver

00:53:56.520 --> 00:53:57.930 align:middle line:90%
under the pillow.

00:53:57.930 --> 00:54:00.180 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well, that
sounds quite right if you're

00:54:00.180 --> 00:54:03.077 align:middle line:84%
expecting a Japanese military
person to come by with a gun.

00:54:03.077 --> 00:54:04.410 align:middle line:90%
Of course, you want to be ready.

00:54:04.410 --> 00:54:06.660 align:middle line:84%
But said, no, that wasn't
why we kept the revolvers.

00:54:06.660 --> 00:54:09.060 align:middle line:84%
We kept them because
of these really tall

00:54:09.060 --> 00:54:12.492 align:middle line:84%
18-foot-tall people, these
giants with massive red hair.

00:54:12.492 --> 00:54:14.700 align:middle line:84%
And the local villagers,
they weren't afraid of them,

00:54:14.700 --> 00:54:16.410 align:middle line:84%
but they scared
the hell out of us.

00:54:16.410 --> 00:54:18.330 align:middle line:84%
Military people
don't talk like that.

00:54:18.330 --> 00:54:19.680 align:middle line:90%
That's why I love these stories.

00:54:19.680 --> 00:54:21.660 align:middle line:84%
And today in the
Solomon Islands,

00:54:21.660 --> 00:54:24.270 align:middle line:84%
which are really quite
remote within themselves--

00:54:24.270 --> 00:54:27.450 align:middle line:84%
I mean, most of it's forested,
mosquito-infested, tons

00:54:27.450 --> 00:54:29.430 align:middle line:84%
of snakes everywhere,
very mountainous,

00:54:29.430 --> 00:54:31.260 align:middle line:84%
it's hard to get
into the interior.

00:54:31.260 --> 00:54:33.600 align:middle line:84%
And the local villagers will
say, well, once in a while

00:54:33.600 --> 00:54:35.303 align:middle line:84%
we'll be driving along
a mountain track.

00:54:35.303 --> 00:54:36.720 align:middle line:84%
The truck will
start off the road.

00:54:36.720 --> 00:54:37.860 align:middle line:90%
It rolls over.

00:54:37.860 --> 00:54:40.140 align:middle line:84%
We'll have to go back 15
miles to the local village

00:54:40.140 --> 00:54:42.090 align:middle line:84%
to get a truck to winch
the whole thing out.

00:54:42.090 --> 00:54:43.590 align:middle line:90%
We go back the following day.

00:54:43.590 --> 00:54:46.590 align:middle line:84%
The truck is back on
the road, upright.

00:54:46.590 --> 00:54:47.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: With its load intact.

00:54:47.890 --> 00:54:49.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: With the load intact.

00:54:49.140 --> 00:54:49.940 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:54:49.940 --> 00:54:51.720 align:middle line:84%
As if a bunch of eggs
have been spilled.

00:54:51.720 --> 00:54:53.650 align:middle line:84%
They put the eggs back,
that kind of thing.

00:54:53.650 --> 00:54:54.960 align:middle line:90%
And they said, it's the giants.

00:54:54.960 --> 00:54:55.950 align:middle line:90%
They're actually very helpful.

00:54:55.950 --> 00:54:56.760 align:middle line:90%
They're very shy.

00:54:56.760 --> 00:54:59.600 align:middle line:84%
And we leave them alone
and they leave us alone.

00:54:59.600 --> 00:55:01.490 align:middle line:90%
It's a lovely entendre.

00:55:01.490 --> 00:55:04.100 align:middle line:84%
And they said that they get
from A to B across the Solomon

00:55:04.100 --> 00:55:05.750 align:middle line:84%
Islands through
the tunnels, which

00:55:05.750 --> 00:55:08.160 align:middle line:84%
are made out of the
limestone, which is fine.

00:55:08.160 --> 00:55:10.040 align:middle line:84%
But the tunnels are
self-illuminating.

00:55:10.040 --> 00:55:13.363 align:middle line:84%
There's something within
the actual crystal or quartz

00:55:13.363 --> 00:55:14.780 align:middle line:84%
structure or the
mineral structure

00:55:14.780 --> 00:55:17.270 align:middle line:84%
of the rock which allows
them to be self-illuminating.

00:55:17.270 --> 00:55:20.240 align:middle line:84%
And the other time I found
that story is actually

00:55:20.240 --> 00:55:23.480 align:middle line:84%
in the Bible, which was, again,
lifted from the Mesopotamian

00:55:23.480 --> 00:55:24.380 align:middle line:90%
tradition.

00:55:24.380 --> 00:55:26.210 align:middle line:90%
That's been proven to be true.

00:55:26.210 --> 00:55:29.270 align:middle line:84%
They talk about Yima, who was
like a prototype for Noah.

00:55:29.270 --> 00:55:31.670 align:middle line:84%
And they said that in order
to see inside the ark,

00:55:31.670 --> 00:55:34.010 align:middle line:84%
they had a window which
was-- or a light that

00:55:34.010 --> 00:55:36.420 align:middle line:90%
was self-shining from within.

00:55:36.420 --> 00:55:39.758 align:middle line:84%
So some kind of rock that they
knew that gave a certain light.

00:55:39.758 --> 00:55:41.300 align:middle line:84%
And they said in
the Solomon Islands,

00:55:41.300 --> 00:55:44.120 align:middle line:84%
this is how they get around from
A to B through the mountains.

00:55:44.120 --> 00:55:45.543 align:middle line:90%
And we're quite happy with them.

00:55:45.543 --> 00:55:47.210 align:middle line:84%
They just want to be
left by themselves.

00:55:47.210 --> 00:55:48.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I love this story.

00:55:48.510 --> 00:55:50.090 align:middle line:84%
Let's bring it back
to Sardinia now.

00:55:50.090 --> 00:55:52.460 align:middle line:84%
We have another of the
nuraghe we want to go to,

00:55:52.460 --> 00:55:53.985 align:middle line:90%
and it's the most famous one.

00:55:53.985 --> 00:55:55.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, when you look
at it from above,

00:55:55.610 --> 00:55:58.575 align:middle line:84%
it raises a lot of questions
like, who were these people?

00:55:58.575 --> 00:55:59.450 align:middle line:90%
Where were they from?

00:55:59.450 --> 00:56:02.540 align:middle line:84%
Because this looks almost like
ancient Celtic structures.

00:56:02.540 --> 00:56:06.530 align:middle line:84%
But first of all,
this site, we need

00:56:06.530 --> 00:56:09.680 align:middle line:84%
to just state we had a whole
day scheduled with sites

00:56:09.680 --> 00:56:12.410 align:middle line:90%
in the South of Sardinia, OK?

00:56:12.410 --> 00:56:15.020 align:middle line:90%
And we had been OKed.

00:56:15.020 --> 00:56:18.388 align:middle line:84%
And then all of a sudden
the boss comes along.

00:56:18.388 --> 00:56:19.430 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what he did.

00:56:19.430 --> 00:56:20.240 align:middle line:90%
Must have looked around.

00:56:20.240 --> 00:56:22.782 align:middle line:84%
Must have had bad experiences
with American production teams.

00:56:22.782 --> 00:56:23.820 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:56:23.820 --> 00:56:25.250 align:middle line:84%
But all our permits
were canceled.

00:56:25.250 --> 00:56:28.670 align:middle line:84%
All of them, including the
most famous site, Barumini.

00:56:28.670 --> 00:56:31.470 align:middle line:84%
But it was our good luck because
we got something even better.

00:56:31.470 --> 00:56:34.400 align:middle line:84%
And that's-- I believe in
things working out the way

00:56:34.400 --> 00:56:35.330 align:middle line:90%
they're supposed to.

00:56:35.330 --> 00:56:35.820 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

00:56:35.820 --> 00:56:37.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So even though we
were grumbling, we thought,

00:56:37.790 --> 00:56:39.500 align:middle line:84%
we can't shoot it,
but we're going

00:56:39.500 --> 00:56:41.810 align:middle line:84%
to go over and at
least as tourists

00:56:41.810 --> 00:56:43.880 align:middle line:90%
take some pictures of this site.

00:56:43.880 --> 00:56:45.050 align:middle line:90%
Look at this from above.

00:56:45.050 --> 00:56:46.940 align:middle line:90%
It's just absolutely incredible.

00:56:46.940 --> 00:56:51.890 align:middle line:84%
But this was the Barumini
nuraghe, the famous Barumini.

00:56:51.890 --> 00:56:55.130 align:middle line:10%
Let's just go ahead and touch
on the dating that you had done,

00:56:55.130 --> 00:56:56.240 align:middle line:10%
your projections for it.

00:56:56.240 --> 00:56:58.310 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Oh, I was quite
happy with 6000 BC.

00:56:58.310 --> 00:56:59.900 align:middle line:90%
I thought, this is pretty good.

00:56:59.900 --> 00:57:02.480 align:middle line:84%
But again, you don't put your
projections into anything.

00:57:02.480 --> 00:57:04.970 align:middle line:84%
You've got to let the
information and the evidence

00:57:04.970 --> 00:57:06.480 align:middle line:90%
follow its own course.

00:57:06.480 --> 00:57:08.220 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, it would
be easy to do.

00:57:08.220 --> 00:57:10.880 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking at the
alignment of Barumini

00:57:10.880 --> 00:57:12.120 align:middle line:90%
and I thought, wait a minute.

00:57:12.120 --> 00:57:13.982 align:middle line:84%
This is just going
off towards the south.

00:57:13.982 --> 00:57:15.440 align:middle line:84%
The alignment is
towards the south.

00:57:15.440 --> 00:57:19.158 align:middle line:84%
What the hell could be aligned
towards the south at that era?

00:57:19.158 --> 00:57:20.450 align:middle line:90%
And of course, nothing matches.

00:57:20.450 --> 00:57:23.370 align:middle line:84%
There's no connection to
sunrises or moonrises,

00:57:23.370 --> 00:57:26.630 align:middle line:84%
which is usually a safe place
to go with sacred sites.

00:57:26.630 --> 00:57:30.980 align:middle line:84%
Now we're getting to
7300 BC and the rising

00:57:30.980 --> 00:57:32.930 align:middle line:84%
of Orion's belt
over the horizon,

00:57:32.930 --> 00:57:35.143 align:middle line:84%
exactly through a gap in
the distant mountains.

00:57:35.143 --> 00:57:37.310 align:middle line:84%
These things were actually
placed very strategically

00:57:37.310 --> 00:57:39.337 align:middle line:90%
to take the landscape.

00:57:39.337 --> 00:57:40.920 align:middle line:84%
So the landscape
becomes part of the--

00:57:40.920 --> 00:57:41.060 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:57:41.060 --> 00:57:41.810 align:middle line:90%
Utilizing the landscape.

00:57:41.810 --> 00:57:44.330 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: You have to go there
to actually look at the site

00:57:44.330 --> 00:57:46.100 align:middle line:84%
and see what they were
looking at because then it

00:57:46.100 --> 00:57:46.975 align:middle line:90%
makes a lot of sense.

00:57:46.975 --> 00:57:48.737 align:middle line:90%
You can't do this on a computer.

00:57:48.737 --> 00:57:50.570 align:middle line:84%
And that's what blew
my mind, that there was

00:57:50.570 --> 00:57:52.280 align:middle line:90%
an even earlier culture here.

00:57:52.280 --> 00:57:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And we're slowly
moving back in time.

00:57:54.410 --> 00:57:58.760 align:middle line:84%
And the earliest-- the oldest
I ever found here in Sardinia

00:57:58.760 --> 00:58:01.160 align:middle line:90%
was about 7500 so far.

00:58:01.160 --> 00:58:04.820 align:middle line:84%
And that's over 24
sites I've analyzed,

00:58:04.820 --> 00:58:06.150 align:middle line:90%
and there's thousands of them.

00:58:06.150 --> 00:58:08.340 align:middle line:84%
So god knows what
else is still to come.

00:58:08.340 --> 00:58:11.360 align:middle line:84%
But it definitely looks
like it's been extended

00:58:11.360 --> 00:58:12.650 align:middle line:90%
from a central tower again.

00:58:12.650 --> 00:58:14.300 align:middle line:90%
You get the sense of power.

00:58:14.300 --> 00:58:17.300 align:middle line:84%
But then again, you've got all
these other towers and myriad

00:58:17.300 --> 00:58:18.890 align:middle line:84%
of labyrinths that
have been added,

00:58:18.890 --> 00:58:20.000 align:middle line:90%
and that's what we're getting--

00:58:20.000 --> 00:58:21.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: These circles
after circle after circle.

00:58:21.620 --> 00:58:21.800 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:58:21.800 --> 00:58:23.330 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Discombobulated stuff.

00:58:23.330 --> 00:58:25.670 align:middle line:84%
I did feel that, yes, there
was a time there was--

00:58:25.670 --> 00:58:27.860 align:middle line:84%
the place looked like it
was sieged at one point.

00:58:27.860 --> 00:58:31.010 align:middle line:84%
And you get that sense
of siege, of fear.

00:58:31.010 --> 00:58:32.900 align:middle line:84%
People were going to
die of starvation.

00:58:32.900 --> 00:58:35.180 align:middle line:84%
And I get that at
Teotihuacan as well.

00:58:35.180 --> 00:58:37.070 align:middle line:84%
That's why I never
go to Teotihuacan.

00:58:37.070 --> 00:58:40.895 align:middle line:84%
I'd love to go, but I can't
get over all the sacrifices

00:58:40.895 --> 00:58:42.020 align:middle line:90%
that were being done there.

00:58:42.020 --> 00:58:43.850 align:middle line:90%
50,000 people killed in one day.

00:58:43.850 --> 00:58:45.320 align:middle line:90%
I can't get past that.

00:58:45.320 --> 00:58:47.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, the
remote viewing team

00:58:47.660 --> 00:58:49.220 align:middle line:84%
couldn't get past
the feelings of it.

00:58:49.220 --> 00:58:52.820 align:middle line:84%
Let's also take a moment just
to view some of the drawings

00:58:52.820 --> 00:58:56.300 align:middle line:84%
that the remote viewers did
of Barumini in that area.

00:58:56.300 --> 00:58:58.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, they did the
same thing about Ruju

00:58:58.700 --> 00:59:01.430 align:middle line:84%
up north and all these
conical structures.

00:59:01.430 --> 00:59:03.470 align:middle line:84%
You can see they
were pretty right on.

00:59:03.470 --> 00:59:05.525 align:middle line:84%
Let's see what Angela
had to say about that.

00:59:05.525 --> 00:59:08.420 align:middle line:84%
She was the one that gave
us the condensed report.

00:59:08.420 --> 00:59:09.985 align:middle line:84%
Angela, hey, it's
so good to see you.

00:59:09.985 --> 00:59:11.360 align:middle line:84%
>>ANGELA THOMPSON:
It's very nice

00:59:11.360 --> 00:59:13.100 align:middle line:84%
to be here and meet
you again, Regina.

00:59:13.100 --> 00:59:13.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:59:13.900 --> 00:59:17.630 align:middle line:84%
And I'm in a 16th century
hotel room in Sardinia

00:59:17.630 --> 00:59:19.890 align:middle line:90%
and open rafters all around me.

00:59:19.890 --> 00:59:21.427 align:middle line:84%
And I'm glad we
have Wi-Fi signal.

00:59:21.427 --> 00:59:22.760 align:middle line:90%
There was some concern about it.

00:59:22.760 --> 00:59:26.780 align:middle line:84%
But let's talk about how
we got together on this

00:59:26.780 --> 00:59:28.850 align:middle line:84%
and what you were
tasked with doing

00:59:28.850 --> 00:59:30.740 align:middle line:84%
as just a little
background for people that

00:59:30.740 --> 00:59:32.360 align:middle line:90%
are looking at this right now.

00:59:32.360 --> 00:59:34.610 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: You had mentioned
that there was a project

00:59:34.610 --> 00:59:38.720 align:middle line:84%
that you would like some remote
viewers to look at and send me

00:59:38.720 --> 00:59:43.080 align:middle line:84%
some background information,
some nonleading coordinates, et

00:59:43.080 --> 00:59:43.880 align:middle line:90%
cetera.

00:59:43.880 --> 00:59:47.840 align:middle line:84%
And I sent that out
to six other viewers,

00:59:47.840 --> 00:59:52.700 align:middle line:84%
and then I had two operational
training students that I also

00:59:52.700 --> 00:59:54.530 align:middle line:90%
gave the project to.

00:59:54.530 --> 00:59:58.040 align:middle line:10%
Most of them used
controlled remote viewing,

00:59:58.040 --> 00:59:59.780 align:middle line:10%
which is a method
that was developed

00:59:59.780 --> 01:00:03.710 align:middle line:10%
by Ingo Swann and Harold Puthoff
at Stanford Research Institute.

01:00:03.710 --> 01:00:08.360 align:middle line:84%
And it's a sequential
written and verbal process.

01:00:08.360 --> 01:00:10.340 align:middle line:84%
You have a stack of
white paper and a pen,

01:00:10.340 --> 01:00:15.080 align:middle line:84%
and you go through a process
accessing more and more

01:00:15.080 --> 01:00:16.520 align:middle line:90%
detailed information.

01:00:16.520 --> 01:00:19.070 align:middle line:10%
And I was really impressed
with what the viewers had

01:00:19.070 --> 01:00:22.430 align:middle line:10%
got, particularly their
sketches and their descriptions

01:00:22.430 --> 01:00:25.080 align:middle line:10%
of the first two locations.

01:00:25.080 --> 01:00:25.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

01:00:25.880 --> 01:00:28.460 align:middle line:84%
They really did do a
good, credible job.

01:00:28.460 --> 01:00:30.350 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about
what they perceived

01:00:30.350 --> 01:00:33.470 align:middle line:84%
as some of the functions
of these, particularly

01:00:33.470 --> 01:00:36.170 align:middle line:84%
where we're looking at
the clusters of circular--

01:00:36.170 --> 01:00:37.550 align:middle line:90%
stone circles.

01:00:37.550 --> 01:00:41.000 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMPSON: The
primary function they

01:00:41.000 --> 01:00:42.710 align:middle line:90%
saw was really as a defense.

01:00:42.710 --> 01:00:44.660 align:middle line:90%
It was like a fort.

01:00:44.660 --> 01:00:46.580 align:middle line:84%
These were for
people to go inside,

01:00:46.580 --> 01:00:49.620 align:middle line:90%
to cluster inside if need be.

01:00:49.620 --> 01:00:52.370 align:middle line:84%
But there were also
very spiritual aspects,

01:00:52.370 --> 01:00:54.570 align:middle line:90%
that these were perhaps tombs.

01:00:54.570 --> 01:00:58.490 align:middle line:84%
They were spiritual temples
almost in some respect.

01:00:58.490 --> 01:01:00.710 align:middle line:84%
So there was very much
a spiritual aspect

01:01:00.710 --> 01:01:03.710 align:middle line:84%
to the whole-- of
both complexes.

01:01:03.710 --> 01:01:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And so there were just multiple
uses for these locations.

01:01:08.430 --> 01:01:10.500 align:middle line:84%
They weren't like
Stonehenge that

01:01:10.500 --> 01:01:13.293 align:middle line:84%
would have been an
iconic place where

01:01:13.293 --> 01:01:15.210 align:middle line:84%
they went to look at the
sun, moon, and stars,

01:01:15.210 --> 01:01:17.370 align:middle line:90%
although that came up too.

01:01:17.370 --> 01:01:19.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That there were
astronomical alignments, yes.

01:01:19.710 --> 01:01:21.168 align:middle line:10%
>>THOMPSON:
Astronomical alignment,

01:01:21.168 --> 01:01:22.860 align:middle line:10%
but that wasn't
their sole function.

01:01:22.860 --> 01:01:26.800 align:middle line:10%
They served a very practical
purpose for the people.

01:01:26.800 --> 01:01:27.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

01:01:27.600 --> 01:01:29.970 align:middle line:84%
And some of them talked
about this energetic use

01:01:29.970 --> 01:01:32.310 align:middle line:84%
that was of a consciousness
that we may not understand

01:01:32.310 --> 01:01:33.570 align:middle line:90%
at this point in time.

01:01:33.570 --> 01:01:33.900 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMPSON: Yeah.

01:01:33.900 --> 01:01:35.340 align:middle line:84%
So there was more
that was hidden

01:01:35.340 --> 01:01:38.400 align:middle line:84%
knowledge, hidden spiritual
knowledge at the site.

01:01:38.400 --> 01:01:41.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What's interesting
is these remote viewers aren't

01:01:41.220 --> 01:01:43.920 align:middle line:84%
given any information,
not even coordinates.

01:01:43.920 --> 01:01:44.880 align:middle line:90%
They get a code.

01:01:44.880 --> 01:01:45.680 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

01:01:45.680 --> 01:01:47.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then she
knows underneath it

01:01:47.790 --> 01:01:50.280 align:middle line:84%
where the coordinates
are, but they don't know.

01:01:50.280 --> 01:01:52.615 align:middle line:84%
They're doing cold
reads, military-style.

01:01:52.615 --> 01:01:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting
what you see here.

01:01:54.240 --> 01:01:57.100 align:middle line:84%
They found they did not
like the feeling of it.

01:01:57.100 --> 01:01:59.460 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, back to what
I was saying earlier,

01:01:59.460 --> 01:02:02.850 align:middle line:84%
Angela's read on it was
these very, very hardy

01:02:02.850 --> 01:02:06.150 align:middle line:84%
and with some knowledge people
had traveled from the north,

01:02:06.150 --> 01:02:08.370 align:middle line:84%
and it almost seemed to
be they were bringing

01:02:08.370 --> 01:02:12.430 align:middle line:84%
a technology with them similar
to the old Saxon ruins and such

01:02:12.430 --> 01:02:14.910 align:middle line:84%
and these stone
circular walls and such.

01:02:14.910 --> 01:02:20.100 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about the notion of
where the people may have come

01:02:20.100 --> 01:02:22.320 align:middle line:84%
from because there
are-- again, it's

01:02:22.320 --> 01:02:24.100 align:middle line:84%
civilization on top
of civilization.

01:02:24.100 --> 01:02:24.900 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

01:02:24.900 --> 01:02:27.900 align:middle line:84%
And the names change over time,
which makes it really difficult

01:02:27.900 --> 01:02:29.545 align:middle line:90%
to figure out.

01:02:29.545 --> 01:02:31.920 align:middle line:84%
The one that keeps coming up
again and again because it's

01:02:31.920 --> 01:02:35.100 align:middle line:84%
one of the few surviving
written stories, which ends up

01:02:35.100 --> 01:02:37.320 align:middle line:84%
being the Book of Enoch,
which is-- there's

01:02:37.320 --> 01:02:39.960 align:middle line:84%
a very old version
of that in Ethiopian.

01:02:39.960 --> 01:02:41.580 align:middle line:84%
Not that I read
Ethiopian, but if you

01:02:41.580 --> 01:02:44.460 align:middle line:84%
want to get the real story
before it becomes Christianized

01:02:44.460 --> 01:02:47.970 align:middle line:84%
or Hebrewized, you have to go
back to the origin of the story

01:02:47.970 --> 01:02:49.500 align:middle line:90%
before the politics kicks in.

01:02:49.500 --> 01:02:52.180 align:middle line:84%
And the Babylonians said the
same thing about this as well.

01:02:52.180 --> 01:02:55.800 align:middle line:10%
And they seem to be centered
somewhere around the Caucasus

01:02:55.800 --> 01:02:58.890 align:middle line:10%
region, somewhere between
the Black Sea and the Caspian

01:02:58.890 --> 01:03:02.490 align:middle line:10%
Sea where ironically, a lot
of the DNA of the skulls

01:03:02.490 --> 01:03:05.370 align:middle line:10%
from Caracas in Peru with
the long heads, their DNA

01:03:05.370 --> 01:03:06.580 align:middle line:10%
goes back to that region.

01:03:06.580 --> 01:03:09.330 align:middle line:10%
Well, if we follow some of
the stories from the Egyptians

01:03:09.330 --> 01:03:11.383 align:middle line:10%
and the followers of
Horus who essentially

01:03:11.383 --> 01:03:12.300 align:middle line:10%
were the same people--

01:03:12.300 --> 01:03:14.092 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: The Shining
Ones, the same group,

01:03:14.092 --> 01:03:16.740 align:middle line:10%
which is the realm of the
sun, the representatives that

01:03:16.740 --> 01:03:19.290 align:middle line:10%
come to help from the realm
of the sun into our dimension.

01:03:19.290 --> 01:03:20.090 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

01:03:20.090 --> 01:03:22.595 align:middle line:84%
And they were also
fascinated with Orion.

01:03:22.595 --> 01:03:23.970 align:middle line:84%
And then you have
a Roman emperor

01:03:23.970 --> 01:03:26.010 align:middle line:84%
that talks about the
Scythian culture, which comes

01:03:26.010 --> 01:03:27.120 align:middle line:90%
from around the Black Sea.

01:03:27.120 --> 01:03:29.370 align:middle line:90%
And he says this offhand remark.

01:03:29.370 --> 01:03:31.083 align:middle line:84%
They're even older
than the Egyptians.

01:03:31.083 --> 01:03:33.000 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking, this
must be the same people

01:03:33.000 --> 01:03:34.418 align:middle line:90%
called the Anu at one point.

01:03:34.418 --> 01:03:36.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turns out that
actually, they are.

01:03:36.210 --> 01:03:38.640 align:middle line:84%
The Scythians and the
Anu are the same people.

01:03:38.640 --> 01:03:42.010 align:middle line:84%
And when they began to
go west through Europe

01:03:42.010 --> 01:03:44.610 align:middle line:84%
as the ice is melting
through Central Europe--

01:03:44.610 --> 01:03:46.710 align:middle line:84%
we're now back at the
end of the Ice Age--

01:03:46.710 --> 01:03:49.350 align:middle line:84%
they start giving the
names to the places.

01:03:49.350 --> 01:03:51.760 align:middle line:90%
For example, the River Danube.

01:03:51.760 --> 01:03:54.660 align:middle line:84%
The river, the Danube,
which then becomes--

01:03:54.660 --> 01:03:55.570 align:middle line:90%
it goes westwards.

01:03:55.570 --> 01:03:57.090 align:middle line:84%
It becomes the
people of the Anu,

01:03:57.090 --> 01:03:58.900 align:middle line:90%
which becomes Tuatha de Danaan.

01:03:58.900 --> 01:03:59.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

01:03:59.700 --> 01:04:01.230 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And from there,
from Central Europe

01:04:01.230 --> 01:04:04.112 align:middle line:84%
they go southwards towards the--
they were looking for an island

01:04:04.112 --> 01:04:05.820 align:middle line:84%
again, I'm sure,
because again, they want

01:04:05.820 --> 01:04:07.600 align:middle line:90%
to recreate their former world.

01:04:07.600 --> 01:04:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And back then,
Sardinia and Corsica

01:04:09.930 --> 01:04:11.550 align:middle line:90%
were actually connected.

01:04:11.550 --> 01:04:13.770 align:middle line:84%
And that would have made
a very, very large piece

01:04:13.770 --> 01:04:14.670 align:middle line:90%
of real estate.

01:04:14.670 --> 01:04:17.190 align:middle line:84%
And that's where the
essence of the people coming

01:04:17.190 --> 01:04:20.190 align:middle line:84%
from the north, from Europe,
ended up in Sardinia.

01:04:20.190 --> 01:04:21.600 align:middle line:84%
So that seems to
match what the--

01:04:21.600 --> 01:04:23.017 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
very interesting.

01:04:23.017 --> 01:04:24.767 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to
confirm that with Angela

01:04:24.767 --> 01:04:26.850 align:middle line:84%
because she's not aware
of what we're finding yet.

01:04:26.850 --> 01:04:27.250 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, good.

01:04:27.250 --> 01:04:28.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we're
going to go both ways

01:04:28.270 --> 01:04:30.103 align:middle line:84%
and have another
conversation with her about

01:04:30.103 --> 01:04:32.550 align:middle line:84%
that because she was very clear
in, what was the strongest

01:04:32.550 --> 01:04:33.090 align:middle line:90%
thing she got?

01:04:33.090 --> 01:04:35.970 align:middle line:84%
It was the migratory path of the
people coming into this region.

01:04:35.970 --> 01:04:38.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, we don't know if there
are the same influences

01:04:38.700 --> 01:04:41.490 align:middle line:84%
up north where we were
at the other nuraghe we

01:04:41.490 --> 01:04:42.760 align:middle line:90%
were in a little bit ago.

01:04:42.760 --> 01:04:47.850 align:middle line:84%
So right at this point, we know
that there are 20,000 to 30,000

01:04:47.850 --> 01:04:49.530 align:middle line:84%
of these things
around the island.

01:04:49.530 --> 01:04:53.160 align:middle line:84%
We've learned that the deeper we
go into the foundations of it,

01:04:53.160 --> 01:04:54.840 align:middle line:84%
the more sophisticated
and advanced

01:04:54.840 --> 01:04:56.320 align:middle line:90%
the culture appeared to be.

01:04:56.320 --> 01:05:00.210 align:middle line:84%
You would go so far as saying
it does appear that acoustics--

01:05:00.210 --> 01:05:02.460 align:middle line:84%
which are mentioned in the
Bible and other texts--

01:05:02.460 --> 01:05:04.800 align:middle line:84%
acoustics were
probably known and used

01:05:04.800 --> 01:05:06.890 align:middle line:90%
to move these massive stones.

01:05:06.890 --> 01:05:07.890 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, absolutely.

01:05:07.890 --> 01:05:10.080 align:middle line:84%
Every culture talks
about the rocks

01:05:10.080 --> 01:05:14.280 align:middle line:84%
being moved to the sound
of a voice or a trumpet.

01:05:14.280 --> 01:05:17.010 align:middle line:84%
And again, if you go
to Central America,

01:05:17.010 --> 01:05:20.130 align:middle line:84%
they do talk about the
Waru or the Huari, who

01:05:20.130 --> 01:05:22.380 align:middle line:90%
were the megalithic builders.

01:05:22.380 --> 01:05:23.820 align:middle line:84%
Except that if you
go to Polynesia

01:05:23.820 --> 01:05:25.320 align:middle line:84%
and you mention
that word of Huari

01:05:25.320 --> 01:05:26.970 align:middle line:84%
they say, actually,
that's a trumpet.

01:05:26.970 --> 01:05:28.230 align:middle line:90%
The Waru is a trumpet.

01:05:28.230 --> 01:05:30.870 align:middle line:84%
And in Central America and
South America with the Shining

01:05:30.870 --> 01:05:34.560 align:middle line:84%
Ones who were the helpers of
Viracocha and his seven people,

01:05:34.560 --> 01:05:36.780 align:middle line:84%
they said that, yes,
we used the trumpets

01:05:36.780 --> 01:05:39.000 align:middle line:90%
to move the stones from A to B.

01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:42.960 align:middle line:84%
And there's a wonderful
parallel here in modern life

01:05:42.960 --> 01:05:45.778 align:middle line:84%
where about 20 years ago,
Princeton of all people,

01:05:45.778 --> 01:05:47.820 align:middle line:84%
there's a certain laboratory
that actually looked

01:05:47.820 --> 01:05:50.220 align:middle line:84%
at the composition of
the stone primarily used

01:05:50.220 --> 01:05:51.195 align:middle line:90%
in these temples.

01:05:51.195 --> 01:05:52.980 align:middle line:84%
It has a specific
type of quartz.

01:05:52.980 --> 01:05:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And they actually threw sound
frequency at a lump of quartz,

01:05:56.010 --> 01:05:57.750 align:middle line:90%
and the lump gets to levitate.

01:05:57.750 --> 01:05:58.980 align:middle line:90%
So we're now coming--

01:05:58.980 --> 01:06:01.260 align:middle line:84%
science is now finally
beginning to catch up

01:06:01.260 --> 01:06:04.020 align:middle line:84%
with 12,000 years of
myth and tradition

01:06:04.020 --> 01:06:06.410 align:middle line:84%
that, yes, these things were
literally built overnight.

01:06:06.410 --> 01:06:08.630 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, even the
whole area of cymatics,

01:06:08.630 --> 01:06:12.770 align:middle line:84%
just watching these beautiful
geometrical movements take

01:06:12.770 --> 01:06:14.420 align:middle line:90%
place in the sand to sound.

01:06:14.420 --> 01:06:17.360 align:middle line:84%
And so there are many ways
in which in the modern world

01:06:17.360 --> 01:06:19.920 align:middle line:84%
we're beginning to prove
that sound can move matter.

01:06:19.920 --> 01:06:20.720 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

01:06:20.720 --> 01:06:22.580 align:middle line:84%
And also the fact that
it's the geometry of sound

01:06:22.580 --> 01:06:24.920 align:middle line:84%
as well, because when sound
hits a physical medium you

01:06:24.920 --> 01:06:25.950 align:middle line:90%
get the sacred geometry.

01:06:25.950 --> 01:06:26.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

01:06:26.750 --> 01:06:28.640 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And they
again looked at nature.

01:06:28.640 --> 01:06:30.920 align:middle line:84%
This is what I'm talking
about, how these people--

01:06:30.920 --> 01:06:32.870 align:middle line:84%
even here in
Sardinia they'll say,

01:06:32.870 --> 01:06:35.300 align:middle line:84%
they have complete control
of the laws of nature.

01:06:35.300 --> 01:06:37.460 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you have
that level of control

01:06:37.460 --> 01:06:39.680 align:middle line:84%
you can see things on
a macroscopic level.

01:06:39.680 --> 01:06:41.660 align:middle line:84%
You can see how
sound, when it starts

01:06:41.660 --> 01:06:43.340 align:middle line:90%
to actually go into the--

01:06:43.340 --> 01:06:44.832 align:middle line:90%
let's say this cup, for example.

01:06:44.832 --> 01:06:46.790 align:middle line:84%
If you're looking at this
under the microscope,

01:06:46.790 --> 01:06:49.490 align:middle line:84%
under an electron microscope,
you won't see the physical--

01:06:49.490 --> 01:06:51.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, you can shatter
glass if it's fine glass.

01:06:51.110 --> 01:06:52.318 align:middle line:90%
You shatter glass with sound.

01:06:52.318 --> 01:06:54.530 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Even more
importantly, it's a structure.

01:06:54.530 --> 01:06:57.800 align:middle line:84%
The molecules that make up the
cup, it's geometric in nature.

01:06:57.800 --> 01:07:00.740 align:middle line:84%
And that brings us back to
why these sites are geometric.

01:07:00.740 --> 01:07:02.930 align:middle line:84%
There's a relationship
between the outer walls,

01:07:02.930 --> 01:07:06.650 align:middle line:84%
the inner beehive, and
the corkscrew staircase

01:07:06.650 --> 01:07:07.505 align:middle line:90%
that goes around.

01:07:07.505 --> 01:07:09.380 align:middle line:84%
An architect would say,
well, it's practical.

01:07:09.380 --> 01:07:10.370 align:middle line:90%
Well, yes, it is.

01:07:10.370 --> 01:07:12.050 align:middle line:84%
You have to get to
the top of the tower.

01:07:12.050 --> 01:07:15.320 align:middle line:84%
But it's also the relationship
of the walls to the exterior,

01:07:15.320 --> 01:07:18.170 align:middle line:84%
to the height creates
its own feeling.

01:07:18.170 --> 01:07:19.790 align:middle line:84%
And also, the fact
that the coils--

01:07:19.790 --> 01:07:21.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The coils,
serpentine energy,

01:07:21.530 --> 01:07:22.890 align:middle line:90%
and the way energy moves.

01:07:22.890 --> 01:07:23.690 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:07:23.690 --> 01:07:26.690 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It's a symbol of
the coiled serpent, which

01:07:26.690 --> 01:07:29.510 align:middle line:90%
actually means the sumer.

01:07:29.510 --> 01:07:31.350 align:middle line:84%
That's where the name
Sumeria comes from,

01:07:31.350 --> 01:07:33.920 align:middle line:84%
which is the origin of
the people of the Anu.

01:07:33.920 --> 01:07:36.440 align:middle line:84%
So these things are all
here still in Sardinia.

01:07:36.440 --> 01:07:38.780 align:middle line:84%
You have to look at the
etymology and the shape

01:07:38.780 --> 01:07:39.890 align:middle line:90%
in which things were made.

01:07:39.890 --> 01:07:43.340 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's been just beyond
a treat of discovery for us

01:07:43.340 --> 01:07:45.437 align:middle line:84%
because as I mentioned
before-- it does.

01:07:45.437 --> 01:07:47.270 align:middle line:84%
It really messes with
your head a little bit

01:07:47.270 --> 01:07:48.710 align:middle line:90%
and your perception of life.

01:07:48.710 --> 01:07:51.440 align:middle line:84%
But also again, as I
said, to have it so raw,

01:07:51.440 --> 01:07:53.480 align:middle line:90%
wild, and available to us.

01:07:53.480 --> 01:07:56.610 align:middle line:84%
That's what's allowed you
to get these measurements,

01:07:56.610 --> 01:07:58.530 align:middle line:84%
and I'm very, very
grateful for that.

01:07:58.530 --> 01:08:00.560 align:middle line:84%
But even though we
were not allowed

01:08:00.560 --> 01:08:04.130 align:middle line:84%
to shoot some of the sights in
the south, we were so lucky.

01:08:04.130 --> 01:08:07.080 align:middle line:84%
